title: Mike Birbiglia Live!
description: MIKE BIRBIGLIA is a comedian, storyteller, director and actor who has performed for audiences worldwide, from the Sydney Opera House to Broadway. His most recent shows, The New One, Thank God for Jokes, and My Girlfriend's Boyfriend can be found on Netflix. Additionally, Birbiglia is a filmmaker who wrote, directed, and starred in the films Sleepwalk With Me and Don't Think Twice. Currently he is the host of the weekly podcast, Mike Birbiglia's Working It Out. His first book, "Sleepwalk With Me and Other Painfully True Stories," was a New York Times bestseller, and he is the author of the new book, "The New One: Painfully True Stories from a Reluctant Dad, with poems by J. Hope Stein." As an actor Birbiglia has appeared on Inside Amy Schumer, Girls and Broad City, and in the films Trainwreck, The Fault in Our Stars, and Popstar. He plays Danny Pearson on Orange Is the New Black and Oscar Langstratt on Showtime's Billions.

title: DECADANCE/CHICAGO: Hubbard Street Dance Chicago’s Spring Performance

Randolph, March 12, 14 and 15, 2020. title: 2020 Day & Night of the Living Ales
description: Saturday, March 7th, 2020 afternoon session: 1-5pm ($45) evening session: 6-10pm ($40) Bottom Lounge 1375 W. Lake St. Chicago, IL 60607 The national drink of Great Britain, cask conditioned ales have been served for centuries. Before brewers fell in love with artificial carbonation and filtering, beer was naturally conditioned by yeast in the cask, and served at a temperature warm enough to actually taste the beer. A properly served cask ale is neither cloudy, flat, nor warm; rather it is bright, with a gentle carbonation, and served at cellar temperature. Sample a vast array of different beers at our walk-around tasting featuring the best cask conditioned ales from Chicagoland breweries and specially selected guests. Food will be available for purchase. Casks are handled by the Chicago Beer Society's own experienced cellarmen, trained in the UK to care for and serve real ale. Attendees will vote on their favorites to crown The Champion Real Ales of Chicagoland for 2020! This year we are also bringing back cheese! During the afternoon session Hooks Cheese, Mineral Point Wisconsin, will sample one of its blue cheeses, a sheep milk Gouda, a mixed milk number called Triple Play, and Hooks classic 5-year-old cheddar. For the evening session, Dave Phillips of Cheese and Cheers (and an active member of the Chicago Beer Society) will sample a specially-curated selection of cheddars, blues and odd styles that pair well with cask beer. All the cheeses will be available for purchase at Potash Markets State Street, where Phillips spends his days running the chains gourmet cheese department. Admission includes souvenir tasting glass, cheese samples, program & beer samples. All ticket sales and sessions chosen are final. All beers will be available for both the afternoon and evening sessions. Participating Breweries: All Rise Alter Around the Bend Burning Bush Church Street Dovetail Evil Horse Finch Goose Island Clybourn Brewhouse Goose Island Fulton Street Hailstorm Half Acre Haymarket Hopvine Illuminated Brew Works Imperial Oak Metropolitan Noon Whistle Off Color On Tour Open Outcry Prairie Street Revolution Roaring Table Rock Bottom Chicago Rock Bottom Orland Park Rock Bottom Warrenville Rolling Meadows Farm Brewery Sketchbook Spiteful Tighthead Two Brothers Urban Renewal Werk Force *Note that sometimes beer gets spilled. Brewery participation is subject to change based on factors beyond our control.

title: City Winery Wine School: Intro to Spanish and the Wines of Spain 2/26/20
description:
Ever go on a foreign vacation and wanted to order a glass of wine in the native tongue? Never before done at City Winery, enjoy a 30-minute language instruction course followed by an hour and a half wine class. We’ll guide you through the basics of wine with an interactive, geeky, ‘research’ intensive wine course. Much tasting and wine discussion. All the fun of wine, with a side of education. Practical knowledge. And, most importantly, developing your palate, your wine vocabulary, and sharpening your tasting skills. We’ll share professional tips on what you really need to know about deductive wine tasting, as well as how to translate your wine tasting savvy in the real world. Good times, wine friends. Come on over and get educated!
Course 1 : City Winery Wine School - Intro to the Spanish Language and the Wines of Spain
First in the series featuring Spanish and the wines of Spain!
Take your taste buds on a journey to the Iberian Peninsula, specifically Spain! Here at City Winery Chicago we feel one of the best ways to learn about a country is through its language (and of course through its wine). Join us for an introduction to Spanish followed by a guided wine tasting. Transport yourself to Europe through this interactive course. Chat, interact, taste, and enjoy all of what this abundant wine-growing region has to offer.

title: Job Fair of Chicago
description:
Wednesday, February 26, 2020
10:00AM - 1:00PM
University of Phoenix Chicago Campus
13th Floor, Suite 1300, 203 N. LaSalle Street 
Chicago, IL 60601
 
** Event Hosted at the University of Phoenix Campus for the GENERAL PUBLIC **
 
Pre-Register online at: 
https://catalystcareergroup.com/event/chicago-2-2020/

Plan to attend and meet face-to-face with several of the Chicago area’s finest employers. 

All of the companies at our job fairs have open positions they are seeking to fill.

Positions in the following areas are typically available:
Sales, Customer Service, Call Center, Management, General Business, Marketing, Retail, Administrative, Insurance, Banking, Engineering, Accounting, Finance, Education, Law Enforcement, Government, Military, Hospitality, Human Resources, Technicians, Telemarketing, Healthcare, IT, and more.

Tips for Success:
* Pre-register—Receive notifications of any updates or changes to the event, and receive information about upcoming events in your area.
* Dress professionally—First impressions go a long way.
* Bring multiple copies of your resume.
* Arrive anytime between 10 AM and 1 PM—Plan to spend 45 minutes to 1 hour at the event.
* Bring a friend—All job seekers are welcome.
* Prepare a brief but effective “brag” to let the people you meet with get to know you.
* Keep an open mind—Meet with as many of the companies as you can; you may be pleasantly surprised at what you find.

Remember, the best way to be considered for a position is to meet the hiring managers in person. Plan to attend this event!
 
Pre-Register online at: https://catalystcareergroup.com/event/chicago-2-2020/

title: Music of the Baroque: Rival Divas—Handel & Mozart
description:
Vocal sparks will fly as internationally renowned sopranos Susanna Phillips and Jane Archibald sing music written for the great dueling divas of the Baroque and Classical eras. The rivalries between Francesca Cuzzoni and Faustina Bordoni in Handel’s day, and Caterina Cavalieri and Aloysia Lange in Mozart’s, come to life in a fascinating program of virtuosic arias and duets.

MONDAY, February 24, 2020 7:30 PM
Harris Theater, Chicago
205 E. Randolph

HANDEL
Arias and duets from Alessandro, Admeto, and Tolomeo
MOZART
Arias from The Abduction from the Seraglio and The Impresario

Music of the Baroque Orchestra
Jane Glover, conductor
Susanna Phillips, soprano
Jane Archibald, soprano

Tickets: $25-$85 
Box Office: 312-551-1414

title: Freedom Ride
description:
When the Congress of Racial Equality comes to New Orleans in the sweltering summer of 1961, Sylvie Davenport is torn. Handed a pamphlet and asked to board a Greyhound bus, Sylvie is forced to choose between her academic future and the future of the nation in a story that highlights how far we’ve come and how far we still have left to go.

Tazewell Thompson (Blue, Jubilee) directs Cardiff prize winner Lauren Michelle in this world premiere, developed at Xavier University with the activists who lived the history. Staley Music Director Lidiya Yankovskaya conducts the critically acclaimed Chicago Sinfonietta.

Music & Libretto by Dan Shore

Conducted by Lidiya Yankovskaya
Directed by Tazewell Thompson

World Premiere
Commissioned by Chicago Opera Theater

Featuring the Chicago Sinfonietta

title: In the Realm of Senses
description:
Jeff Yang violin, viola, cello, baroque recorder
Matthew Agnew cello
Lyudmila Lakisova piano

Modest Mussorgsky (arr. Jeff Yang) Pictures at an Exhibition
Maurice Ravel Sonata for Violin and Cello

Enjoy a unique multi-sensory performance of Mussorgsky's "Pictures at an Exhibition." Jeff Yang has transformed this classical music staple, based on the paintings of Viktor Hartmann. Yang’s rendition features two players and eight instruments. Throughout the performance, audiences will experience stunning music paired with animated lithographs by John Gaudette based on the lost paintings of Viktor Hartmann along with other sensory elements. The program will also include Ravel's beautiful, nostalgic duo for violin and cello. This performance will entice your ears, eyes, nose, tastebuds, and more in a completely new and exhilarating way!

title: Freedom Ride
description:
When the Congress of Racial Equality comes to New Orleans in the sweltering summer of 1961, Sylvie Davenport is torn. Handed a pamphlet and asked to board a Greyhound bus, Sylvie is forced to choose between her academic future and the future of the nation in a story that highlights how far we’ve come and how far we still have left to go.

Tazewell Thompson (Blue, Jubilee) directs Cardiff prize winner Lauren Michelle in this world premiere, developed at Xavier University with the activists who lived the history. Staley Music Director Lidiya Yankovskaya conducts the critically acclaimed Chicago Sinfonietta.

Music & Libretto by Dan Shore

Conducted by Lidiya Yankovskaya
Directed by Tazewell Thompson

World Premiere
Commissioned by Chicago Opera Theater

Featuring the Chicago Sinfonietta

title: Catholic Charities Hosts 19th Annual d'Vine Affair
description:
Catholic Charities of the Archdiocese of Chicago hosts the 19th Annual d'Vine Affair, a premier wine and craft beer tasting event held at the Union League Club of Chicago. Guests can sample fine wine and beer from around the world along with gourmet hors d'oeuvres and desserts while supporting the food, clothing, shelter, counseling, and other services that help families on a path to long-term stability.

Sample from more than 90 vintners and breweries, many of whom will be on hand to educate guests on their ingredients and methods. A Wine-Appreciation Seminar kicks off the afternoon. Guests can learn and taste with Kevin Bratt, the Concept Wine Director at Joe's Seafood, Prime Steak & Stone Crab in Chicago, Las Vegas, and Washington D.C. A Craft Beer Seminar will be presented by Samu Rahn, the Specialty Import & Craft Brand Manager for Louis Glunz Beer, Inc. Adding to the festivities will be a wine grab, silent auction and raffle prizes, plus a Live Barrel of Wine Auction, which equals 25 cases of wine. All proceeds from the event will go towards Catholic Charities Self-Sufficiency Programs. For tickets, visit http://www.catholiccharities.net/dvine.

title: Music of the Baroque: Alison Balsom Plays Haydn
description:
Trumpet sensation Alison Balsom wields her “alluring, expressive tone and agile technique” (New York Times) in Haydn’s beloved trumpet concerto. Mozart’s innovative Linz and Prague symphonies and Haydn’s uplifting Alleluia symphony complete this Classical showcase in honor of Mozart’s birthday.

SATURDAY, January 25, 2020 7:30 PM
Harris Theater, Chicago
205 E. Randolph

MOZART
Symphony No. 36 (Linz)
HAYDN
Trumpet Concerto
HAYDN
Symphony No. 30 (Alleluia)
MOZART
Symphony No. 38 (Prague)

Music of the Baroque Orchestra
Jane Glover, conductor
Alison Balsom, trumpet

Tickets: $25-$85 
Box Office: 312-551-1414

Take your tribe into the New Year at the 2020 NYE (New Year’s Eve) Yacht Party taking place Tuesday, December 31, 2019 on the Anita Dee II presented by Social Scene.

From dance parties, top floor DJ, live piano bar & the must-have midnight champagne cheers… the New Year’s Eve Yacht Party is the perfect place to wrap up 2019 and celebrate the kick-off of 2020 with those you care for the most.

Now the real question is… how to choose which FLOOR, MIDNIGHT KISS or a MIDNIGHT FIREWORKS SHOW to ring 2020 to?

title: Sequence Ch!cago
description:
Saturday, October 5 Kick-Off Concert: 5 – 8 p.m. South Dock MUSIC: DJ Shazam Bangles; Ana Ewerling; Brian Hoyt

Sequence Ch!cago returns to Navy Pier this fall and winter, highlighting the city’s vibrant arts and cultural scene over 10 dates throughout the season. Presented by the Paul M. Angell Family Foundation, the series includes performances from Chicago’s gifted musicians, handcrafted works by local artisans and special events, such as “Housegiving,” a house music celebration featuring a clothing drive for the homeless. The series kicks off on Saturday, October 5 and will conclude on Saturday, December 20 with “A Blues Christmas” in the spectacular Aon Grand Ballroom.

title: INTERNATIONAL MUSIC FOUNDATION'S 44TH ANNUAL DO-IT-YOURSELF MESSIAH
description:
A Chicago holiday tradition since 1976, the International Music Foundation's presentation of Do-It-Yourself Messiah brings together a world-class conductor and soloists, an all-volunteer orchestra of local professional and amateur musicians and actively encourages the thousands of audience members to step into the role of the chorus in a thrilling performance of George Frideric Handel’s masterpiece, Messiah.
 
Join us on December 16th and 17th at the Harris Theater for Music and Dance in Millennium Park. Tickets are $15 each and will be on sale at noon on November 15th. Visit  https://www.harristheaterchicago.org/tickets/2019-2020-season/diy-messiah for more details.

title: "Sing! An Irish Christmas"
description:
Sing! An Irish Christmas: Keith & Kristyn Getty With Ricky Skaggs

Join Ireland’s own Keith & Kristyn Getty, known for modern hymns and carols such as “In Christ Alone,” for their ninth-annual tour of Sing! An Irish Christmas. Previously featured on public television to over 45 million US households and in the UK on BBC, this year’s concert has been reinvented around the ten most essential carols in history and will be broadcast internationally to millions of families on the Trinity Broadcast Network. The Gettys are joined by their band of virtuosic instrumentalists fusing Celtic, bluegrass, Americana, modern and classical music along with cultural Irish dance and the choral sounds of the holiday. Come sing along with Keith & Kristyn and special guest Ricky Skaggs for an evening that unites tradition and innovation in a vibrant celebration of the season!

Apollo Chorus Sings Handel’s Sublime Messiah

For two performances only, this Holiday Season the Apollo Chorus of Chicago will perform one of Chicago’s greatest holiday traditions: Händel’s Messiah at the Harris Theater for Music and Dance, Chicago. Audiences flock to hear the thrilling renditions of Händel’s work as some by the Apollo Chorus. This year we’re proud to announce a quartet of internationally-acclaimed soloists, including soprano Amanda Majeski, mezzo-soprano Kayleigh Decker, tenor William Hite, and bass-baritone Darren Stokes.

title: Sequence Ch!cago
description:
Saturday, October 5 Kick-Off Concert: 5 – 8 p.m. South Dock MUSIC: DJ Shazam Bangles; Ana Ewerling; Brian Hoyt

Sequence Ch!cago returns to Navy Pier this fall and winter, highlighting the city’s vibrant arts and cultural scene over 10 dates throughout the season. Presented by the Paul M. Angell Family Foundation, the series includes performances from Chicago’s gifted musicians, handcrafted works by local artisans and special events, such as “Housegiving,” a house music celebration featuring a clothing drive for the homeless. The series kicks off on Saturday, October 5 and will conclude on Saturday, December 20 with “A Blues Christmas” in the spectacular Aon Grand Ballroom.

title: Auditorium Theatre's 130th Birthday Celebration Open House
description: The National Historic Landmark theatre, which officially opened on December 9, 1889, has been a Chicago institution for 130 years. You’re invited to celebrate this milestone anniversary at a FREE Open House! Take a historic theatre tour, pose for a picture at a photo booth with an Auditorium Theatre-themed backdrop; sketch and take photos of the theatre; bring the kids for free popcorn and coloring; grab a drink at the bar; and enter a raffle for a chance to win free tickets to a future Auditorium Theatre performance. Photographs, program books, and posters from the theatre’s archives will also be on display.

title: Chicago Philharmonic presents Marcus Roberts Trio with Orchestra
description:
Chicago Philharmonic turns the heat all the way up with MARCUS ROBERTS TRIO joining the full orchestra onstage at Harris Theater on Sunday, December 8th. Witness the lightning-quick musical reflexes and creative imagination of international jazz superstars Marcus Roberts, Jason Marsalis, and Rodney Jordan as they bring Gershwin's sparkling Piano Concerto in F to life. Plus, the Philharmonic performs Duke Ellington's cheeky, jazzy take on the Nutcracker... wailing saxophones and all! 

Holidays: Marcus Roberts Trio + Orchestra
Sunday, December 8 / 3:00PM
Harris Theater for Music and Dance

Scott Speck conducts the Chicago Philharmonic
Featuring Marcus Roberts, Jason Marsalis, and Rodney Jordan

George Gershwin - Concerto in F
Duke Ellington/Billy Strayhorn - The Nutcracker Suite
Samuel Coleridge-Taylor - Christmas Overture
Pyotr Ilyich Tchaikovsky - December from The Seasons

Tickets $25-$75 | Discounts for students and seniors

title: Sequence Ch!cago
description:
Saturday, October 5 Kick-Off Concert: 5 – 8 p.m. South Dock MUSIC: DJ Shazam Bangles; Ana Ewerling; Brian Hoyt

Sequence Ch!cago returns to Navy Pier this fall and winter, highlighting the city’s vibrant arts and cultural scene over 10 dates throughout the season. Presented by the Paul M. Angell Family Foundation, the series includes performances from Chicago’s gifted musicians, handcrafted works by local artisans and special events, such as “Housegiving,” a house music celebration featuring a clothing drive for the homeless. The series kicks off on Saturday, October 5 and will conclude on Saturday, December 20 with “A Blues Christmas” in the spectacular Aon Grand Ballroom.

title: Sequence Ch!cago
description:
Saturday, October 5 Kick-Off Concert: 5 – 8 p.m. South Dock MUSIC: DJ Shazam Bangles; Ana Ewerling; Brian Hoyt

Sequence Ch!cago returns to Navy Pier this fall and winter, highlighting the city’s vibrant arts and cultural scene over 10 dates throughout the season. Presented by the Paul M. Angell Family Foundation, the series includes performances from Chicago’s gifted musicians, handcrafted works by local artisans and special events, such as “Housegiving,” a house music celebration featuring a clothing drive for the homeless. The series kicks off on Saturday, October 5 and will conclude on Saturday, December 20 with “A Blues Christmas” in the spectacular Aon Grand Ballroom.

title: The Santaland Diaries
description: This holiday season, Goodman Theatre presents The Santaland Diaries-David Sedaris' "vivid, hilarious portrait of family Christmas with his deft combination of wicked humor and scalpel-sharp observation" (Chicago Magazine). Adapted by Joe Mantello and directed by longtime Goodman Artistic Associate Steve Scott, this "theatrical stocking stuffer" (Chicago Reader) is perfect for those who prefer their eggnog spiked. Chicago favorite Matt Crowle makes his Goodman debut in a solo performance as the strapped-for-cash struggling actor who takes a job as "Crumpet," an elf at Macy's Santaland-and his hilarious observations are more naughty than nice.

title: Sequence Ch!cago
description:
Saturday, October 5 Kick-Off Concert: 5 – 8 p.m. South Dock MUSIC: DJ Shazam Bangles; Ana Ewerling; Brian Hoyt

Sequence Ch!cago returns to Navy Pier this fall and winter, highlighting the city’s vibrant arts and cultural scene over 10 dates throughout the season. Presented by the Paul M. Angell Family Foundation, the series includes performances from Chicago’s gifted musicians, handcrafted works by local artisans and special events, such as “Housegiving,” a house music celebration featuring a clothing drive for the homeless. The series kicks off on Saturday, October 5 and will conclude on Saturday, December 20 with “A Blues Christmas” in the spectacular Aon Grand Ballroom.

The Second City’s Improv Comedy Hour

The Second City’s Improv Comedy Hour (it’s more than an hour, but that’s improv) was dreamed up by Mick Napier. He’s famous for tossing out “the rules” in cutting-edge shows like Co-Ed Prison Sluts, the longest-running musical in Chicago. Get there early and grab a spot up close—improv’s famous for involving the audience!

title: Music of the Baroque: Bach and the Italians
description:
Eighteenth-century Italy was a vibrant source of musical inspiration. Nicholas Kraemer leads the orchestra in a colorful program showcasing the genius of the Italian Baroque—and our own principal players—including Marcello’s gorgeous Concerto for oboe and Vivaldi’s triumphant Concerto for 2 trumpets. Concertos for 2 and 3 violins by J. S. Bach show just how far—and how loudly—Italian influence resonated.
Monday, November 25, 2019 7:30 PM
Harris Theater, Chicago
205 E. Randolph

SCARLATTI
Sinfonia in G Major
Sinfonia in B-flat Major
BACH
Concerto in C Major for 3 Violins
MARCELLO
Concerto in D Minor for Oboe
VIVALDI
Concerto for 2 Trumpets
GEMINIANI
Concerto grosso in G Minor, op. 3, no. 2
BACH
Concerto in D Minor for 2 Violins

Music of the Baroque Orchestra
Nicholas Kraemer, conductor

title: 2019 Grandparents Day at Chicago Toy & Game Fair
description:
EXPLORE, DISCOVER & EXPERIENCE!  
Join Us at North America’s Biggest Toy & Game Fair Open to Kids of All Ages! 
Grandparents Day Sunday November 24th! 
Children of all ages are invited to bring their grandparents to the Chicago Toy & Game Fair on Sunday, November 24th. Grandparents attending the Fair with their grandchildren will be welcomed into the Fair free of charge. Just register here and print out your ticket. Grandchildren will need to have a purchased ticket. 
What are you planning for the holidays? Come join us for a wonder-inspiring weekend at the 17th annual Fair brought to you as part of the Chicago Toy & Game (ChiTAG) Week - the largest toy and game fair open to the public in North America! Enjoy the many special events that appeal to all ages 0 to 100!
We showcase the best toys and games from around the globe. Build towers, play in tournaments, meet characters and more! The Chicago Toy & Game Fair is the destination to discover "what's hot for the holidays" and try out toys and games before you shop for Black Friday Specials throughout the holiday season. You are certain to find some great additions to your family collection of toys and games.
Highlights for 2019!  

Young Inventor Challenge
Frozen II Scavenger Hunt
Kids in Frozen costumes on Saturday FREE
Baby and Toddler PlaySpace
Blackhawks Inflatable Rink - Saturday Only
World's Largest Kid-Powered Rocket Debut!
WTTW Big Idea Traveling Lab Performance
Beer Garden with Popular Adult and Party Games
Meet Toy & Game Inventors from Around the World
Gator Golf Putting Station
Fuzzikins Decorate and Take
​My Buddy Wheels Riding Space 
Etch-a-Sketch with Princess-Etch
Photo Ops with  characters from Star Wars!
Shop for New and Classic Toys for the Holidays
Elan Dancers from Naperville Stage Performance
Yo-Yo Championship - Contestants from Coast to Coast
Interactive Exhibits, Test out Products Before They Hit Retail Shelves
Ben’s Giant Bubble Show, Giveaways, Stage Events, Magic Shows, Contests

Are you a Scout, firefighter, police, active military, educator or librarian? Check out our ticketing page for more information on qualifying for free admission. 
Parking and Directions: https://www.chitag.com/directions
Check out other events happening at ChiTAG Week:
Toy & Game Innovation Awards (TAGIEs) ($250)More details: http://www.chitag.com/tagies

title: "The Best Of Second City: Late Night Edition"
description:
The Best Of Second City: Late Night Edition

The Second City is a legendary Chicago comedy company, founded in 1959, that has produced such epic comedy stars as John Belushi, Dan Aykroyd, Gilda Radner, Mike Myers, Tina Fey and Steve Carell. In The Best of The Second City: Late Night Edition, some of the company’s most talented up-and-coming comedians draw on over half a century of comedy history to present classic sketches and songs from all eras of The Second City, plus new material and improvised scenes. This show at UP Comedy Club has a rotating cast all summer, so you’ll never see the same show twice!

title: 2019 New Inventor & New Business Track of the Innovation Conference
description:
Since 2008, our Inventor Conference has been the largest event for toy and game inventors. This is your opportunity to pitch your ideas directly to top toy and game execs, product acquisition and inventor relations executives from companies such as the ones featured above. These companies were looking for new ideas last year and we expect more companies this year!
​We have assembled the most knowledgeable experts in the toy and game industry to give you advice and feedback. This is the one time in the year that many of these inventor relations executives will look at outside submissions from inventors. 
Your registration includes information-packed conference, keynotes and networking events: Inventor Night at the Irish Pub (we take over an entire pub) and the elegant and celebratory Toy & Game Innovation Awards (the TAGIEs). This New Inventor Track a must attend event and space is limited. 
Full Conference ticket includes:

Full access to events at the Conference targeting small companies and new inventor sessions, held in adjacent conference rooms, see New Inventor Track for more details


Networking meals and coffee breaks with Speakers and other Conference attendees
One-minute Speed Pitching – Get your toy, game and playful products ready to do this show-and-tell-speed dating-style! Set-up at a table and top toy & game company executives come to you. 
Please note: The Chicago Toy & Game Group does not claim royalties or commissions on any contracts/agreements made as a result of Conference participation. 
Ticket to the Inventor Night at the Irish pub with toy & game companies executives and Professional Inventors. Great food, great space, great networking, we take over a whole pub! (Valued at $150)
Toy and Game Innovation Awards (TAGIEs) - One ticket -  A seat for each registrant at the 10th annual TAGIEs. Join us for an elegant, celebratory and playful Friday evening. (Valued at $250)
2-days (Saturday & Sunday) admission to the Chicago Toy & Game (ChiTAG) Fair with your Conference badge, ChiTAG Fair is a unique weekend Fair that is open to the public, trade and the media at the start of the 4th quarter holiday shopping season. ChiTAG Fair shows the latest toys, games and a wide variety of playful products offered by our 150+ Exhibitors.  Explore the latest trends in the toy, game and play industry or test out your products by taking advantage of the discounts for  Booth space or table!  
Conference registration gives you discounts on exhibit space at the Chicago Toy & Game Fair:$300 discount on an Inventor Table (6 foot table and 2 chairs) or $500 discount on a 10 x 10 foot or larger Booth space http://www.chitag.com/exhibit-at-the-fair After you regsiter for the conference, just ask us for the special discount code. 

Companion Conference Ticket includes:
The Companion Ticket includes all the previous benefits except for the exhibit table for 1-minute Speed pitching since it is assumed they are part of the team for the first ticket. Companion Registration can only be purchased paired with a Full New Inventor Conference Registration. There is a cancelation fee due to costs with eventbrite, authorize.net, credit card processing and our accountants. We are charged but all parties in both the registration and in the credit processing. 
*Participating companies subject to change.
Parking and Directions: https://www.chitag.com/directions
SPACE IS LIMITED! DON'T MISS OUT!

title: Connected Insurance USA 2019
description:
Connected Insurance USA is bringing the leaders from across the insurance organization to seize the opportunity and become an agile, customer-centric and digitally transformed carrier.

Since the year 2000, 50 percent of the Fortune 500 companies have disappeared as they failed to stay relevant and competitive in the digital economy.

The time's up for siloed thinking and siloed structures. Outdated products and clunky service are no longer acceptable.

Survival and future success rely on embedding speed to address customer challenges faster than the competition, merging innovative technology with real-time data to transform product, underwriting, customer experience and claims.

This is the only event in the world providing insurance carriers with the necessary strategies to transform each core pillar of Product Development, Innovative Tech and Customer Engagement, as one to deliver what the connected customer is demanding: personalized products, real-time engagement and seamless service.

title: Everest/Aleko
description:
A modern masterpiece and a Romantic Russian gem come together in a massive double-bill.

Moby-Dick stars Andrew Bidlack (Greenhorn) and Aleksey Bogdanov (Starbuck) return to the COT stage in the musical event of the season. Over 150 choristers join a full orchestra onstage to bring Joby Talbot and Gene Scheer’s critically acclaimed Everest and Rachmaninov’s beautiful Aleko to Chicago for the first time.

In Joby Talbot and Gene Scheer’s Everest, based on the true story chronicled in Jon Krakauer’s critically acclaimed book Into Thin Air, a team of climbers set out to summit the monolithic mountain. Plagued by the ghosts of those claimed by the journey, they endeavor to join the hallowed ranks of adventurers to have conquered the peak.

In Rachmaninov’s Aleko, a man abandons a life in Russian society to join his love, the fiercely independent Zemfira, and her free spirited camp of Romani travelers. When Zemfira refuses to settle down with just one lover, Aleko is faced with a choice: adapt to this new life, or face tragic consequences.

Everest
Music by Joby Talbot
Libretto by Gene Scheer
Commissioned by The Dallas Opera

Aleko
Music by Sergei Rachmaninov
Libretto by Vladimir Nemirovech Danchenko

Conducted by Lidiya Yankovskaya
Directed by Dylan Evans

In partnership with A&A; Ballet and Apollo Chorus Of Chicago

title: Sequence Ch!cago
description:
Saturday, October 5 Kick-Off Concert: 5 – 8 p.m. South Dock MUSIC: DJ Shazam Bangles; Ana Ewerling; Brian Hoyt

Sequence Ch!cago returns to Navy Pier this fall and winter, highlighting the city’s vibrant arts and cultural scene over 10 dates throughout the season. Presented by the Paul M. Angell Family Foundation, the series includes performances from Chicago’s gifted musicians, handcrafted works by local artisans and special events, such as “Housegiving,” a house music celebration featuring a clothing drive for the homeless. The series kicks off on Saturday, October 5 and will conclude on Saturday, December 20 with “A Blues Christmas” in the spectacular Aon Grand Ballroom.

title: FreightWaves LIVE Chicago
description:
Want to learn and get caught up to date with all of the trends affecting freight? FreightWaves LIVE is the premier event in freight, designed to provide you with industry leaders' views of the key factors affecting freight markets and discussions on how the market is shaping up for 2020 and beyond.
Being held November 12–13 at at Chicago's McCormick Place Convention Center, the largest convention center in North America, FreightWaves LIVE Chicago will feature:


Fast-paced demos of cutting-edge freight technologies


Networking with some of the top minds and thinkers in the freight industry


Key market insights from industry leaders to help you prepare for the future


Day one will feature cutting-edge, short-form demos from dozens of freight-tech startups, demonstrating the very latest in technological innovation shaping the freight industry. These rapid-fire demos provide a proven platform for freight-tech companies to achieve the next level of success with new customers, establish strategic partnerships, gain expert feedback, receive press coverage, and secure VC funding.  
Day two will provide the latest thinking on the economics of freight markets from industry visionaries. Keynotes and panels will provide high-level strategic and  actionable insights, giving you the best competitive intelligence on the economics of the freight markets for 2020 and beyond. 
Attendees can expect to meet: 


Senior-level transportation industry executives, venture capitalists, industry analysts, developers, press, bloggers, and entrepreneurs from across the industry spectrum


Decision makers behind the biggest brands and startups who create buzz around high-impact technology across all industry segments: shippers, carriers, 3PLs, supply chain management, manufacturing, and media

title: SAP Conference for Treasury Management
description:
SAP solutions can help organizations to optimize digital transformation to gain better control of treasury management - maximizing visibility of cash flow, liquidity and risk. 

The event will kick off with 2 full-day and 4 half-day, deep-dive, pre-conference workshops. Topics to be covered will include: 
- End-to-End Treasury Management with S/4HANA  
- Managing Cash, Payments and Bank Communications with SAP S/4HANA
- SAP S/4 HANA Cloud
- Working Capital Management
- End-to-End Process for FX Risk Management in SAP Treasury Management
- Intelligent Finance:Changing the world of Finance with SAP Machine Learning

Each workshop offers a unique opportunity to address challenges and gain valuable guidance from some of the most knowledgeable experts on SAP applications. The workshops will be followed by the main conference, with sessions covering key topics such as:
• Digital Transformation
• Intelligent Finance
• Working Capital Management
• FX Risk Management
• Multi-Bank Connectivity
• Cash Management and Payments
• Commodity Management
• Trade Finance
• Exposure Management
• Cash Forecasting
• Liquidity Planning
• Predictive Analytics 
• Machine Learning
• Treasury Reporting
• SAP Cloud Platform

Hear implementation case studies from high profile SAP customers such as Google, NextEra Energy, Autodesk, HP and more!
Also on offer will be SAP solution update sessions; interactive micro-forums covering innovation; a vibrant exhibition showcasing SAP implementation partners and a not-to-be-missed evening networking soiree.

By attending this event, you will learn how SAP solutions for Treasury Management will allow your treasury department to:
1. Reduce Risk 
2. Simplify and Optimize Processes 
3. Enable Growth 
4. Streamline and Centralize Policies 
5. Increase Efficiency 
6. Achieve Automation
7. Embrace Digital Transformation

Visit the official web site to find out more information about the event and register: http://bit.ly/2lLGbko.

Time: 9:30 am to 3:45 pm

Speakers: Google, NextEra Energy, HP, Autodesk

title: Cyber Insurance USA 2019
description:
With the rapid expansion of the cyber insurance market, carriers compete by expanding coverage without charging additional premium - taking on a significant risk. Can predictive modelling be the solution to creating a sustainable pricing model and reducing your aggregate risk exposure?

Join Insurance Nexus as they host Evan Fenaroli, Cyber Product Manager, Philadelphia Insurance Companies and Sean Clifford, Senior Underwriter, Professional Liability Team, Berkshire Hathaway - to discuss how to stay competitive while maintaining a sustainable stance, build and utilize loss data effectively, use predictive modelling to anticipate exposure, and discover the future evolution of pricing models.

title: Sequence Ch!cago
description:
Saturday, October 5 Kick-Off Concert: 5 – 8 p.m. South Dock MUSIC: DJ Shazam Bangles; Ana Ewerling; Brian Hoyt

Sequence Ch!cago returns to Navy Pier this fall and winter, highlighting the city’s vibrant arts and cultural scene over 10 dates throughout the season. Presented by the Paul M. Angell Family Foundation, the series includes performances from Chicago’s gifted musicians, handcrafted works by local artisans and special events, such as “Housegiving,” a house music celebration featuring a clothing drive for the homeless. The series kicks off on Saturday, October 5 and will conclude on Saturday, December 20 with “A Blues Christmas” in the spectacular Aon Grand Ballroom.

title: Giordano Dance Fall Series
description:
Giordano Dance Fall Series

Giordano Dance Chicago (GDC) presents a world-premiere work created by beloved choreographer Peter Chu on the Harris Theater’s stage. Chu adds his signature finesse with bold, liquid movement to the powerful GDC repertoire along with other works selected by masterful programmatic engineer, Artistic Director Nan Giordano. Witness the return of “Can’t Take This Away” by Randy Duncan, a deeply moving and spiritual work featuring live vocals by the Bourné Family, find the light of hope with Marinda Davis’ “Flickers,” and enjoy Alberto Arias’ classically smooth “Surrender,” being pulled from the Company’s repertory vault after a 20-year hiatus. Lauded as “one of our city’s foremost cultural treasures” by See Chicago Dance, GDC’s performances promise to astound even the most seasoned dance enthusiast. Join America’s original jazz dance company at the Harris Theater.

title: Music of the Baroque: "The Chase"
description:
Music of the Baroque: The Chase — Haydn, Handel & Rameau

In the 18th century, hunting was more than a leisure activity — it was a symbol of power, virility, and even good government. Nicholas Kraemer leads an evocative program that brings “the hunt” to life, including the hunting scene in Rameau’s Hippolyte et Aricie, Haydn’s Chase Symphony, and Bach’s Hunt Cantata.

title: SAP Conference on Central Finance, October 2019, Chicago, IL
description:
Pre-conference workshops, customer case studies, group discussions, roadmap and solution updates from SAP will demonstrate how you can utilize the power of one. By establishing one single source of data and one standard process via the SAP S/4HANA Central Finance deployment, users are simplifying their financial processes, lowering operational costs, as well as achieving better business transparency and visibility of productivity.

The SAP Conference on Central Finance is designed for SAP prospects and customers across a full range of global industries. The specific focus in each of these organizations however is on simplifying complex financial landscapes and establishing a centralized source of truth for financial data. The event will also be of value to SAP partners and consultants working within the industry. This conference presents a unique opportunity to meet with both business and IT professionals, including:

VP's, Heads of, Directors for:

- Finance Operations (Payables, Receivables, Cash management)
- Finance Centralization (Shared Services)
- Merger and Acquisition, Divestitures, Post-Merger Integration
- Finance Transformation
- Financial Controll
- Finance, Planning and Analysis (FPandA)
- Accounting (Non-operational)

Other Job Titles Are Set to Include:

- CFO, CIO, Finance IT Manager, Director IT Finance, Senior Consultant SAP Finance

Event highlights will include:

- Informative Keynote Speakers
- Multi Industry Case Studies
- Deep Dive Workshops
- Interactive Sessions
- Ample Networking Opportunities
- Fun and Relaxing Celebration Evening
- Vibrant Partner Exhibition 
- Expert Advice and Dedicated Q and A

Speakers: Cargill, Stanley Black and Decker Inc., Hewlett Packard Enterprise, Karl Storz, Verizon, Owens Corning

title: Columbia College Chicago’s Dance Presenting Series Presents  d. Sabela grimes  ELECTROGYNOUS
description:
Columbia College Chicago’s Dance Presenting Series Presents

d. Sabela grimes

ELECTROGYNOUS

“One of a mere handful of artists who makeup the vanguard of hip-hop fusion..”

-Los Angeles Times

d. Sabela grimes

ELECTROGYNOUS

*first time appearing in Chicago

Thursday-Saturday, October 10-12, 2019

7:30PM

Dance Center of Columbia College

1306 S Michigan Ave

*Post Performance Conversation: Thursday, October 10

a conversation immediately following the performance with the artists

“Black pain is very profitable in this country; we are focused on black joy.” -d. Sabela grimes

Keeping with this seasons idea of creating and fostering of connection through dance, the Presenting Series is excited to present d. Sabela grimes. After years as a company member with hip-hop pioneer Rennie Harris, grimes has developed a movement system derived from black vernacular social-dance practices, music, activism, and their interconnectedness. ELECTROGYNOUS imagines the inclusion of liberated Black bodies at the celebratory center of the work. Featuring video art by Meena Murugesan and digital illustration by Mr. Maxx Moses, ELECTROGYNOUS brings new speculative realities to the stage.

About the Dance Center: The Dance Center of Columbia College Chicago is the city’s leading presenter of contemporary dance, showcasing artists of regional, national and international significance. The Dance Center has been named “Chicago’s Best Dance Theatre” by Chicago magazine, “Best Dance Venue” by the Chicago Reader and Chicago’s top dance venue by Newcity, and Time Out Chicago cited it as “…consistently offering one of Chicago’s strongest lineups of contemporary and experimental touring dance companies.” The Dance Presenting Series recently celebrated 45 years of presenting contemporary dance in Chicago.

About d. Sabela grimes:

d. Sabela grimes, 2017 County of Los Angeles Performing Arts Fellow and 2014 United States Artists RockefellerFellow, is a trans-media storyteller, sonic ARKivist, movement composer cultivating a devoted interest in Afrobiquitous life practices. Sabela has conceived, written, scored, choreographed and produced several dancetheater works including BulletProof Deli, plus Philly XP, World War WhatEver, and 40 Acres & A Microchip:Salvation or Servitude from his EXPERIMENT EARTH sound-movement triptych. Recent creative projects include, ELECTROGYNOUS (2017) and Dark Matter Messages (2018). ELECTROGYNOUS is a dance theater experience which articulates that Black gender qualities are infinite, multidimensional and distinct manifestations of wombniversal consciousness. Moved by how Octavia E. Butler invents interrelated

notions of humanness+otherness in her Parable Series, Dark Matter Messages dreams Butler's unfinished manuscript, Parable of theTrickster, into an experience that realizes quantum Blackness as a means to play within the nowness of imminent futures. On faculty at USC’s Glorya Kaufman School of Dance, he continues to cultivate, Funkamental MediKinetics,a movement system he created that focuses on the methodical dance training and community building elements evident in Hip Hop, Black vernacular and Street dance forms. Sabela loves pancakes, speculative fiction and his kinfolk. dsabelagrimes.com

Funding Credit:

The Dance Center presentation of d. Sabela grimes is made possible by the New England Foundation for the Arts’ National Dance Project, with lead funding from the Doris Duke Charitable Foundation and The Andrew W. Mellon Foundation. Additional support is provided by the National Endowment for the Arts.

d. Sabela grimes / dsabelagrimes.com

title: "Daughter of a Cuban Revolutionary"
description:
Daughter of a Cuban Revolutionary

This solo tour de force tells an astonishing tale centered on three towering figures in the life of performer Marissa Chibas: her father, Raul Chibas, who co-wrote the manifesto for the Cuban revolution with Fidel Castro; her uncle, Eddy Chibas, who was the frontrunner for presidency in 1951 before committing suicide during a live radio broadcast; and her mother, Dalia Chibas, Miss Cuba runner-up in 1959. Zigzagging through her own stories and key episodes in the history of her illustrious family, Chibas gives an impassioned, live wire performance that is propelled by her near-death experience in the Venezuelan Amazonia.

title: Columbia College Chicago’s Dance Presenting Series Presents  d. Sabela grimes  ELECTROGYNOUS
description:
Columbia College Chicago’s Dance Presenting Series Presents

d. Sabela grimes

ELECTROGYNOUS

“One of a mere handful of artists who makeup the vanguard of hip-hop fusion..”

-Los Angeles Times

d. Sabela grimes

ELECTROGYNOUS

*first time appearing in Chicago

Thursday-Saturday, October 10-12, 2019

7:30PM

Dance Center of Columbia College

1306 S Michigan Ave

*Post Performance Conversation: Thursday, October 10

a conversation immediately following the performance with the artists

“Black pain is very profitable in this country; we are focused on black joy.” -d. Sabela grimes

Keeping with this seasons idea of creating and fostering of connection through dance, the Presenting Series is excited to present d. Sabela grimes. After years as a company member with hip-hop pioneer Rennie Harris, grimes has developed a movement system derived from black vernacular social-dance practices, music, activism, and their interconnectedness. ELECTROGYNOUS imagines the inclusion of liberated Black bodies at the celebratory center of the work. Featuring video art by Meena Murugesan and digital illustration by Mr. Maxx Moses, ELECTROGYNOUS brings new speculative realities to the stage.

About the Dance Center: The Dance Center of Columbia College Chicago is the city’s leading presenter of contemporary dance, showcasing artists of regional, national and international significance. The Dance Center has been named “Chicago’s Best Dance Theatre” by Chicago magazine, “Best Dance Venue” by the Chicago Reader and Chicago’s top dance venue by Newcity, and Time Out Chicago cited it as “…consistently offering one of Chicago’s strongest lineups of contemporary and experimental touring dance companies.” The Dance Presenting Series recently celebrated 45 years of presenting contemporary dance in Chicago.

About d. Sabela grimes:

d. Sabela grimes, 2017 County of Los Angeles Performing Arts Fellow and 2014 United States Artists RockefellerFellow, is a trans-media storyteller, sonic ARKivist, movement composer cultivating a devoted interest in Afrobiquitous life practices. Sabela has conceived, written, scored, choreographed and produced several dancetheater works including BulletProof Deli, plus Philly XP, World War WhatEver, and 40 Acres & A Microchip:Salvation or Servitude from his EXPERIMENT EARTH sound-movement triptych. Recent creative projects include, ELECTROGYNOUS (2017) and Dark Matter Messages (2018). ELECTROGYNOUS is a dance theater experience which articulates that Black gender qualities are infinite, multidimensional and distinct manifestations of wombniversal consciousness. Moved by how Octavia E. Butler invents interrelated

notions of humanness+otherness in her Parable Series, Dark Matter Messages dreams Butler's unfinished manuscript, Parable of theTrickster, into an experience that realizes quantum Blackness as a means to play within the nowness of imminent futures. On faculty at USC’s Glorya Kaufman School of Dance, he continues to cultivate, Funkamental MediKinetics,a movement system he created that focuses on the methodical dance training and community building elements evident in Hip Hop, Black vernacular and Street dance forms. Sabela loves pancakes, speculative fiction and his kinfolk. dsabelagrimes.com

Funding Credit:

The Dance Center presentation of d. Sabela grimes is made possible by the New England Foundation for the Arts’ National Dance Project, with lead funding from the Doris Duke Charitable Foundation and The Andrew W. Mellon Foundation. Additional support is provided by the National Endowment for the Arts.

title: THE MAKEUP SHOW CHICAGO
description:
The Makeup Show returns to Chicago!!  Experience the largest pro beauty event filled with top brands in Hair, Skin, Makeup as well as legendary makeup artists. Enjoy our educational opportunities on the Main, Seminar and Demo Stages, Hands-on Workshops & introducing our newly added Momentum Session Series.
Meet the CEOs & Executives behind the brands and stock up on all the essential products from large, indie, pro and prestige brands offering pro discount prices for your makeup kit and retail line up and watch demo and seminar stages.
Brand include: Smashbox Cosmetics. Perricone MD. Ardell Beauty. Temptu. Stila. Pacifica Beauty. Kryolan. Moira Cosmetics. Alcone. Crown Brush. Purlisse Beauty. Danessa Myricks Beauty. MUSE Beauty. Pro. Frends Beauty. Marmalade Nails. Glamcor. Pinnacle Cosmetics. Ruby May Cosmetics. Mario Badescu. and MORE! 

FAQs
Who can attend The Makeup Show?
Makeup Lovers, Makeup Artist, Retail/ Counter Artist & Specialist in Beauty, Cosmetologists, Nail Technicians, Estheticians, Hairstylists, Beauty/Fashion Students, Barbers, Fashion Stylist, Buyers, Beauty Executive, Product Developers, Photographers, Models, Aspiring Artist, Beauty Supply & Apothecary Owners & Employees, Salon and Spa Management and staff, Fashion and Costume Designers ,Wholesale & Distributers for Hair & Beauty Cosmetics , Actors, Dancers. and anyone else that love makeup as much as we do.
Note: 
One Day Tickets grant you entrance to The Makeup Show on either Saturday 5th or Sunday 6th. 
Two Days Tickets grant you entrance to The Makeup Show on both Saturday 5th or Sunday 6th.

Is there a minimum age requirements to enter the event?
No minimum age requirment however attendees must bring ID plus proof of credentials. 
What's included with your ticket?
Your ticket includes acces to pro discounts on the exhibitor floor, Main Floor Seminars, Demos and Main Stage Presentations.
Visit https://www.themakeupshow.com/chicago/ for further details on educational opportunity and Guest Speakers or email Sophia@themakeupshow.com to purchase Hands-On Workshops after ticket purchase. 
Do I have to bring my printed ticket to the event?
Yes, or show your ticket on your phone. 
I bought a Saturday Ticket but I can only attend Sunday or vice versa?
Your one day ticket grants you access to the show on either Saturday or Sunday. A two day ticket grants you access to the show on both days.
What are my transportation/parking options for getting to and from the event?
Please check out: https://www.themakeupshow.com/chicago/travel/
What's the refund policy? 
There are no refunds on tickets. 
How can I contact the organizer with any questions?
email Joanni@themakeupshow.com or Sophia@themakeupshow.com. 
Please Visit https://www.themakeupshow.com/chicago/exhibitors/ for a full list of our Exhibitors, Special Guest Speakers, Education Opportunities and much more. See you at the Show!

title: Flu Shots & Drink Shots -- Immunology @ a Bar!
description:
Get your flu shot – Get a drink shot! Seriously.
It’s easy to procrastinate getting your annual flu shot. If you didn't get yours yet, ISC is making it soooo easy for you! Even if you already got yours, you certainly have friends who haven’t, maybe because they’re nervous, skeptical, or think they don’t need it. You need to bring them to this program where they can get all their questions answered, in person, by real science experts. 
You’ll be rewarded with a free drink as well for being a public health hero!
Have a drink, learn the real deal about vaccines, then get your flu shot. Done!
Get answers to these and all your vaccine questions:

How are antibiotics different from vaccines and how do they work?
Why does it have to be a shot and can’t be a pill?
Why should I get a vaccine for something as mild as the flu?
Can’t I get sick from a flu shot? I’m scared of a serious reaction.
Why every year? Why not just one good one as a kid like chicken pox?
Little babies can’t handle lots of shots because they’re delicate, right?
Why are there vaccines for measles and flu but not Zika, Ebola, AIDS, or Herpes?
Can’t I just change my diet to boost my immune system and not get sick?
Your questions!

IL Science Council's Experts:
Susan Ross, PhD, Virologist, Professor at University of Illinois at Chicago 
Steven Piecyk, Pharm.D., Pharmacy Manager, Jewel-Osco Pharmacy 
   * A sign language interpreter from the Chicago Hearing Society will be available during the program.  
Doors open at 6:00pm; Program at 7:00pm.Food & drink are available for purchase at Haymarket.Tickets are $15 in advance and $20 day of.Ticket includes 1 free drink (does not need to be a shot; can be soda, coffee, a house beer, well cocktail or wine)
After the discussion, guests can get their flu shot in the back room from a licensed Osco pharmacist. Most health insurance plans will cover the flu shot at 100%. To get your shot for free, if you have health insurance, you must bring your health insurance card, or just take a picture of it to keep in your phone to show the pharmacist. A couple limited plans (certain HMOs) will not cover a flu shot at 100%. If you have one of those, or no current insurance, we will have a limited number of flu shots that can be provided at no cost but you must let us know in advance.
Quick & easy; tiny needles; (virtually) painless. Don’t put it off any longer, and be a public health hero!  
 
Illinois Science Council thanks to our great partners! 


If you are interested in event sponsorship, contact Monica at mmetzler@IllinoisScience.org.

SHAPING ORGANIZATIONS WORTH WORKING FOR.
Learn how to put people first and make your organization the envy of your industry.



Today’s talent has different priorities and they want to work with leaders who share them. Workforce values and people-first thinking. These are the building blocks of the modern workplace. Our 2019 Leadership Symposium is the first step in helping you and your organization get there.






In a single day of progressive speakers sharing the latest research and hands-on learning, we’ll help you diagnose the challenges you and your leadership team face and meet the demands of today’s top talent. title: Water For People Blues Bash
description:
Join us for an exciting evening of live music, food, and drinks - all in support of Water For People! 
We'll be at Buddy Guy's Legends in downtown Chicago. Live blues, pop, and RnB will be provided by the NuBlu Band, featuring the daughter of Blues legend Buddy Guy, Carlise Guy. 
Tickets are $40 advance, $50 at the door. Includes two drink tickets and hors d'oeuvres. Proceeds from this event benefit Water For People. 
We're in town for WEFTEC19, but this event is open to everyone - whether or not you're a conference attendee! 



THANK YOU TO OUR GENEROUS BASH SPONSORS!
Silver Sponsors: CDM Smith | Greeley and Hansen
Bronze Sponsor: Black & Veatch

We hope to see you there! Please reach to Julie Kauffman with any questions. 




ABOUT WATER FOR PEOPLEBased in Denver, Colorado, Water For People is a global nonprofit dedicated to providing access to improved water and sanitation systems and services in nine countries. title: EIGHT NIGHTS: A Staged Reading To Benefit HIAS - 9/22/19
description:
8 Nights of EIGHT NIGHTS is a series of staged readings on 8 different nights in 8 different cities, to raise funds and awareness for HIAS and to stand with all those who are persecuted on the basis of race or religion.
EIGHT NIGHTS, a new play by Jennifer Maisel, tells the story of Rebecca, a young Holocaust survivor and refugee, who is finally free to start anew in the United States, but must confront  the past that haunts her.
The play spans eight decades of Rebecca’s life, and touches upon not only the story of Holocaust survivors, but also the global refugee experience. It acknowledges the trauma mirrored in the African-American community, with interned Japanese citizens and the current Syrian crisis, gracefully weaving together heart-aching moments with dark yet life-affirming humor.
If you give voice to the darkness, can you move into the light? Or is history always doomed to repeat itself?
"NIGHT" 5 (brunch performance) at City Winery Chicago will be directed by Jeremy Ohringer and produced by Cara Greene Epstein and Rachel Leventhal.


TICKET LEVELS:

Host Committee $108 - Purchasing a Host Committee ticket helps cover the cost of the staged reading. You get Front Premier seats and your name in the program!
VIP Tickets $72 - VIP and Premium Tickets really make a difference for HIAS!
Premium Tickets $36 - We would love to see you there!


PLEASE NOTE:
No portion of the ticket purchase is tax deductible.
Net proceeds after the cost of the event will be donated to HIAS.
To make additional donations directly to HIAS: http://bit.ly/8NightsOfEightNights-HIAS-Fundraiser

title: Grand Cochon
description:
Sunday, September 15th from 6pm - 8:30pm (VIP starts at 5pm)
Tickets: General Admission, $150; VIP, $225

Grand Cochon, is the epic finale to the multi-city touring culinary competition. The winner will be crowned the "King or Queen of Pork" on Sunday evening, September 15th for the competition's 10th anniversary. Grand Cochon brings together the winning chefs of regional competitions - the outcome is a friendly competition featuring more than 2,500 pounds of heritage pork raised by American family farmers. The event will feature celebrated chefs and nose-to-tail cookery representing an array of cultures, cities and cooking styles. Each of the chefs is tasked with preparing the best 3 bites of heritage breed pig from the whole-animal menu they created to win their respective cities. The event is akin to a 40-course stand-up tasting menu, with dozens of competition plates served alongside artisan wines, boutique spirits, handcrafted cocktails, and some of the best cheeses, charcuterie, sweets, and pop-up food experiences the country has to offer. 

2019 competitors are: Bruno Davaillon, Buillon (Dallas); EJ Miller, International Smoke (Houston); Daniel Espinoza, Cantina Loredo (Chicago); Gabriel Erales, Comedor (Austin); Scott Hergott, Sky Bistro (Banff); Seung Joon Choi (NYC); Scott Pampuch, 4 Bells (Minneapolis); Jorgie Ramos, Barley (Miami); Brian Redzikowski, Kettner Exchange (Los Angeles). A portion of all sales will benefit Grand Cochon's sister charity Piggy Bank.

title: ALS Walk for Life
description:
Join the Les Turner ALS Foundation for the ALS Walk for Life on September 15, 2019, at Soldier Field. The 2-mile course winds along Chicago’s lakefront and through iconic Solider Field. Emceed by Phil Schwarz of ABC7 and Melissa McGurren of 101.9FM THE MIX, the event will include food, music, entertainment and children’s activities. 

Most participants walk as teams in honor of a loved one living with ALS or in memory of someone who has passed away from the disease. The event is a day of celebration, hope and courage with people walking for hope, walking for help and walking for life.  

With approximately 7,000 participants, the ALS Walk for Life is Chicagoland’s largest gathering of the ALS community. Registration is free, and participants are encouraged to fundraise for the Les Turner ALS Foundation. Parking is available in the Solider Field garages.

To register or learn more, visit www.alswalkforlife.org or contact the Les Turner ALS Foundation at 847-679-3311.

title: Music of the Baroque: Mass in B Minor
description:
Music of the Baroque: Mass in B Minor
Written across two decades and completed in Bach’s final years, the Mass in B Minor is the glorious summation of an extraordinary musical life. Jane Glover leads the chorus, orchestra, and a roster of top-notch Bach soloists in one of the greatest creative achievements of all time.

205 E. Randolph

Jane Glover, conductor
Yulia Van Doren, soprano
Krisztina Szabó, soprano

title: CIOarena Chicago 2019
description:
CIOarena™ summits are world-class technology events; providing attendees with expert insights that can be integrated into their professional roles to help optimize and secure their organizations. CIOarena™ will unite Chicago-area IT executives and professionals in a day of intimate networking, industry-led discussions, and a delicious five star breakfast and lunch. Explore the most relevant topics in IT today, in an executive driven educational format.  

The most successful executives will agree that a key attribute to growing ones professional profile, is the power to develop key relationships both internally and externally. CIOarena is designed to take you to the next step in strategic relationship building via our intimate peer-to-peer networking sessions. All attendees are local to the Chicago Metropolitan area, thus enabling you to boost your career by developing strategic relationships within your community, while comparing and contrasting the successes and pitfalls of peers across all industries and disciplines. 

Become a transformational leader by leveraging the newest technologies for a competitive advantage. The insights and best practices shared by our renowned industry experts will guide you in the right direction and the knowledge you walk away with is invaluable. CIOarena's short, no-frills agenda ensures that you reap maximum reward with minimal time wasted. As an invitation-only conference, there is no cost to attend CIOarena. This amazing conference is funded through the support of 10 key sponsors and contributors. In order to provide the best experience possible, CIOarena is a vendor-limited environment with no more than 10 vendors at any one event.
 
*In order to provide a standard of excellence, CIOarena is an invitation/referral-only conference. If you have not been referred by a current guest or contacted by one of our event organizers, your registration will need to be reviewed and approved by the organizer. You must meet teh below criteria to register without an invitation from our team. A CIOarena representative will reach out to you in the event that your registration is approved or not approved. 
 




Pre-Requisites to Register








Must bear an IT/tech-related title at the manager level and above (e.g. Manager, Director, VP, CXO, Head, etc)


Title can not be related to sales, marketing, consulting, recruiting, or of the such


Companies smaller than 50 people must be reviewed prior to confirmation


Organization may not be from an IT vendor, IT solution provider, or IT consulting firm, unless revenue exceeds $750 million in revenue


Company must have a valid company domain (no personal emails) and a functioning website


All of the above must be true unless you have received a personal invite to attend

title: A&A; Ballet Open Auditions for “The Art Deco Nutcracker”
description:
Audition attire: Girls-black camisole leotard, pink footed tights, pink canvas ballet and pointe shoes (age/level appropriate); Boys-black footed tights, white tight fitted t-shirt, black ballet shoes. The audition will include some basic dance movement and a combination to be performed in character. No preparation of audition material is necessary. Dancers will be notified via email within the week after the audition if they have been cast. A production fee will be required for dancers performing “The Art Deco Nutcracker” and varies depending on role. Rehearsals begin in September and will take place primarily on Saturdays at the American Rhythm Center. A pre-registration form may be downloaded at aacenterfordance.org. 

Set in 1920s America, Kremnev's “The Art Deco Nutcracker,” featuring Tchaikovsky’s beloved score, is a fresh, yet traditional take on the beloved holiday favorite. “The Art Deco Nutcracker” is Kremnev's eighth full-length ballet. His work has been presented at the world-renowned Bolshoi Theatre in Moscow, Lincoln Center in New York, and the Opernhaus Zurich in Switzerland, among other prestigious venues across the globe. Tickets for Kremnev's “The Art Deco Nutcracker” go on sale at a later date to be announced.

title: Cardio Obstetrics Symposium
description:
The program features a world-renowned faculty of cardiologists, cardiac surgeons, obstetricians and anesthesiologists with a long-standing experience in the management of pregnancy associated cardiovascular conditions. The purpose of the symposium is to provide a state of the art, comprehensive review of important topics related to congenital and acquired cardiovascular diseases in pregnancy. The two days program will include didactic reviews of a wide spectrum of topics followed by multidisciplinary panel discussions and case presentations with audience participation.

We are looking forward for your participation in this exiting meeting.

Uri Elkayam, MD, Professor of Medicine, Professor of Obstetrics and Gynecology, Director Maternal Cardiology
University of Southern California, Los Angeles, California
Avraham Shotan, MD, Clinical Associate Professor of Cardiology, Rapaport Medical School, Technion, Haifa, Israel.

Speakers: Uri Elkayam, Avraham Shotan, Dianne L Zwicke, Danna Spears, Candice Silversides, Hartzell V. Shaff , Marla Mendelson, Afshan Hameed, Heidi Connolly, Patrick M. Colletti, Joan Briller, Katherine W. Arendt

title: First Chair Awards Conference & Gala 2019
description:
The annual First Chair awards program now in its eighth year, is a full day conference program followed by an evening awards gala. It has become the must‐attend event for in‐house counsel and their partners in the private legal community. Attended by more than 500 attorneys from around the country, this event will honor in‐house counsel from some of the country’s most recognized companies who have made significant contributions to the legal community.
The event includes a full day of CLE programming presented by First Chair faculty for our in‐house counsel community and select sponsors. The full‐day event will include a General Counsel Panel followed by a private luncheon. Thereafter, attendees will be able to choose from a number of Breakout Sessions led by top law firm practitioners and members of the in‐house community.
After the Conference, First Chair will host its 2019 Award Gala at Venue SIX10, A truly spectacular setting with amazing views of Chicago’s Michigan Avenue from the Hancock Center to Soldier Field. Floor-to-ceiling windows showcase Navy Pier, Millennium Park, Buckingham Fountain, the Museum Campus, and Lake Michigan.
Photo Release: As a registrant, I agree and acknowledge that First Chair Awards Conference & Gala plans to take photographs at the 2019 awards gala and conference and reproduce them in news or promotional material, whether in print, electronic or other media, including the First Chair website (www.firstchairevent.com). By participating in the First Chair Awards Conference & Gala I grant the right to use my name, photograph and biography for such purposes. I am aware this is a release of liability and rights of use related to photographs; a contract between myself and First Chair Awards Conference & Gala 2019. I have read, understand and agree to these terms and am entering into this agreement of my own free will.

title: 2019 LEAP InnovatED Summit
description:
Overview
How did Chicago become the country’s largest demonstration site of personalized learning? What have we figured out along the way? How can we continue to reimagine the boundaries of learning?
The 2019 LEAP InnovatED Summit will explore these questions and many more. The annual conference is a once-a-year chance for educators and education innovators across Chicagoland to share, learn and build a community of practice.
Get InspiredKick off the school year energized. Keynote presentations by national thought leaders and innovators will help attendees anchor on their core values and passions within education, and breakout sessions around specific areas of practice will rally a desire to continue pushing students’ learning to new heights.
Elevate Your PracticeThere’s a lifelong learner in every educator. Summit sessions will give teachers the latest findings in learning science, innovation and education research, packaged with actionable tools and strategies for bringing them to life.
Connect with Innovative ColleaguesCommunity and collaboration have been essential to Chicago’s rise as a national hub of personalized learning. They will be even more essential as we accelerate and expand the learning transformation. At the Summit, attendees can meaningfully connect with peers and partners who share their determination to see that all young people receive the holistic, tailored opportunities they deserve.
Creative, passionate educators are pushing the boundaries of learning across Chicago and driving the national movement to transform education.
Join us!

title: Cottonelle Superior Clean Country Fair
description:
In celebration of National Toilet Paper Day on Mon., Aug. 26, Chicago consumers will enjoy a peachy-clean experience unlike any other, brought to you by Cottonelle and Amazon’s Treasure Truck. Guests who roll on down to North Polk Park within Navy Pier will witness the “Cottonelle Superior Clean Country Fair” filled with a host of clean-themed activities, special guests and more! Activations include:

· Peachy Clean Finger Paint Art: Come leave your mark! Guests will be welcomed to show off their artistic finger painting skills and make their contribution to a number of 3D peach murals placed throughout the fair.

· Arcade Row: Classic arcade games with a peachy twist. Guests can practice their aim with Peach-A-Shot and Peach Bocce and then make their way over to the Prize Booth filled with Peachy Prizes.

· The Upgraded Bathroom Art Gallery: View a showcase of artwork by local artists Nate Baranowski and a selection of artists from Ava Grey Designs as they reinvent the porcelain throne. Guests of the fair are welcomed to admire the works of art and vote on their favorite masterpiece!

· The CleaningRipples Slide: Capture the thrill of sliding down a toilet paper-themed slide in your official Cottonelle Country Fair National Toilet Paper Day 2019 photo.

· How Do You Roll?: Join Cottonelle and influencers Timothy Delaghetto, Justin & Nick, Chantelle Paige-Mulligan, and Judy Travis in a nation-wide over/under poll and help finally answer the age-old question: What’s the proper way to place your toilet paper roll?

title: Bands Across The Water: Lakeside Pride presents the London Gay Symphonic Winds World Tour
description:
Bands Across The Water
Lakeside Pride presents the London Gay Symphonic Winds World Tour

The London Gay Symphonic Winds head across the pond with an eclectic selection of music from Welsh folksong to Lady Gaga. Along with musicians from hometown host Lakeside Pride Music Ensembles, a sibling LGBTQA music group, the performers will fly you around the world with an instrumental story of lands near and far. Symphonic band fans throughout Chicagoland, mark your calendars for this one-night-only performance on Saturday, August 24th!

Saturday, August 24th
7:00 pm - 9:00 pm
Studebaker Theater, 410 South Michigan Ave 
$15
lakesidepride.org/london

Accessibility

Percussion typical of symphonic ensembles will be used. There will not be pyrotechnics, strobe lights, or smoke effects.

Wheelchairs have a flat path from the sidewalk to the main floor of the theater where there is ADA-accessible seating. There is an elevator to the second floor but second floor seating is not ADA-accessible.

ADA-accessible and all-gender restrooms are located on the main floor. Restroom signs are marked with braille.

Programming is presented in English. Sign language interpretation is not provided.

Other accessibility questions can be directed to info@lakesidepride.org. We will make every effort to accommodate needs and incorporate requests in future events.

About Lakeside Pride

Lakeside Pride Music Ensembles is Chicago’s premier family of performance groups for members and friends of the lesbian, gay, bisexual, transgender, and queer (LGBTQ) community. Home to three major ensembles – Jazz Orchestra, Marching Band, and Symphonic Band – plus over a dozen chamber ensembles, the organization offers a diverse musical experience for both its audience and members.

About London Gay Symphonic Winds

The London Gay Symphonic Winds are London’s only symphonic wind band from and for the LGBT communities in London. Their musical aim is to be both fun and challenging. They want to encourage improving musicianship in an enjoyable and supporting environment. They play a wide variety of music to suit their diversity, including band classics, orchestral arrangements, show tunes, and, of course, the odd bit of Abba and Madonna.

title: SPCS Young Professionals Conference: Chicago 2019
description:
We are excited to announce the 2nd Annual Young Professionals Networking Conference on Aug 23rd-25th, 2019 hosted in Downtown Chicago.
Registration is open through now through Aug 16th, 2019, please register. Space is limited!
The SPCS community is filled with knowledgeable, experienced, and driven members who can help young professionals reach their ambitious career goals. Through this networking conference, attendees will have the opportunity to build a robust professional network while also reinforcing the cultural connections that link us together.
Just as the SPCS Conventions have helped you meet new friends and connect with old, the SPCS Young Professionals Conference will help attendees meet new people to build their network in our community.
This conference will cater to those 21-35 years of age. Our goal is to create a strong professional and social network through the SPCS.
Location: Aloft Chicago Mag Mile
The registration fee is inclusive of:

2 night hotel stay at the Aloft hotel including taxes (not including incidentals) - Note: you will be paired with one other person randomly to room with unless otherwise specified during registration
Food for 3 day conference
Group activity on Saturday afternoon

If you have any questions, please contract us using the contact organizer form.
If you would to register without hotel room, please contact us using the contact organizer form.

title: Job Fair of Chicago
description:
Job Fair of Chicago
Wednesday, August 21, 2019
10:00AM - 1:00PM
University of Phoenix Chicago Campus
13th Floor, Suite 1300
203 N. LaSalle Street
Chicago, IL 60601
Reduced price parking at:
200 N. Clark, Chicago, IL
(bring ticket to Univ. of Phoenix for validation)
Plan to attend and meet face-to-face with several of the Chicagoland area’s finest employers.
All of the companies at our job fairs have open positions they are seeking to fill.
Positions in the following areas are typically available:
Sales, Customer Service, Call Center, Management, General Business, Marketing, Retail, Administrative, Insurance, Banking, Engineering, Accounting, Finance, Education, Law Enforcement, Government, Military, Hospitality, Human Resources, Technicians, Telemarketing, Healthcare, IT, and more.
Tips for Success:
Pre-register—Receive notifications of any updates or changes to the event, and receive information about upcoming events in your area.
Dress professionally—First impressions go a long way.
Bring multiple copies of your resume.
Arrive any time between 10AM and 1PM—Plan to spend 45 minutes to 1 hour at the event.
Bring a friend—All job seekers are welcome.
Prepare a brief but effective “brag” to let the people you meet with get to know you.
Keep an open mind—Meet with as many of the companies as you can; you may be pleasantly surprised at what you find.


Remember, the best way to be considered for a position is to meet the hiring managers in person. Plan to attend this event!
Questions?
Phone:  815.308.5426

We hope you can join us in supporting these artists and sharing your feedback afterwards. Each of our choreographers have the option of selling tickets to use this opportunity to fundraise for themselves and their work and/or in order to pay their dancers.
