title: 2019 Opportunity Zone Expo Chicago
description:
Join us in Chicago on August 12th, 2019 for the country's largest Opportunity Zone Expo.
WHAT IS THE OPPORTUNITY ZONE EXPO
Opportunity Zone Expo is the countries largest conference for Developers, Brokers, CPAs, Attorneys, Government Officials, Investors and Real Estate Professionals that have in-depth experience with Opportunity Zones.
The 2019 Opportunity Zone Expo Chicago on August 12, 2019 is part of a national conference series dedicated to Opportunity Zone stakeholders. A myriad of educational panels, moderated by industry experts, helps professionals stay at the forefront of the booming Opportunity Zone industry.
Our Last Opportunity Zone Expo COMPLETELY SOLD OUT with over a THOUSAND ATTENDEES.
CLICK HERE TO CHECK OUT OUR LAST EVENT
WHO WILL ATTEND
Hundreds of Opportunity Zone fund managers, investors, developers, attorneys, finance/accounting professionals, and service providers focused on facilitating qualified opportunity funds.
DISCOUNT TICKETS
Special discounts are available for groups of 3 or more, members of the military, government officials, students and attorneys requiring financial aid. To verify your discount eligibility, call 1-866-329-1895 to speak to a representative.
HOTEL DISCOUNT
Book your hotel room at the Radisson Blu Aqua Hotel, Chicago with our exclusive discounted room block expiring on July 10th.
https://www.radissonblu.com/reservation/itineraryEntrance.do?hotelCode=ILCHIAQU&promotionalCode=OPPZON
Promotional Code: OPPZON
EVENT SCHEDULE

WHY JOIN THE OPPORTUNITY ZONE EXPO


Maximize your return on investment by plugging into a network and accessing the top Qualified Opportunity Funds on the market today.


Investors need accurate legal and tax advice to successfully navigate this new program – attending the expo will provide attendees with the opportunity to meet and network with experienced Opportunity Zone service providers.


Developers and fund managers who have set up Qualified Opportunity Funds will be introduced to a sophisticated network of capital connections and investors seeking investment opportunities.


Project owners seeking operating capital can learn how to form a Qualified Opportunity Fund and connect with knowledgeable tax professionals to get a project started.


Professionals involved in the business of tax services, commercial lending, and other value-added services will elevate their professional brand presence and thought leadership through networking and breakout panels.


Government representatives of Opportunity Zone Census Tracts will find a platform to network with project developers and promote economic development in their communities.


This is an industry that will have a profound impact on tax and capital advisory over the next 10 years. Treasury Secretary Steven Mnuchin has predicted more than $100 billion will be invested through this program. So don’t get left behind by missing the largest national event for Opportunity Zones! 


WHAT PAST ATTENDEES ARE SAYING
"I found the conference to be very impressive in terms of the quality of speakers, panels and networking. I came away with a lot of business cards and made the acquaintance of several other advisors in the space!"

Timothy Trifilo - CohnReznick


"I wanted to let you know that I have found your forum to be the most exciting and compelling repository of thought leadership on the OZ front. You have also created a fabulous team around this and I enjoy working with each of them."

Susan Rounds - Deutsche Bank




"You all did an absolutely great job. You managed to not only provide experts in the field, but you also managed to provide an environment where people can interact and exchange information. GREAT JOB"

Lance Growth - Growth 1031




"It was an amazing event. Great information, great contacts, and you guys put on a first-class exposition. We look forward to future events."

Brent Forsberg - Urban Systems

QUESTIONS?
Call us at 1-866-329-1895 or visit www.opportunityzoneexpo.com for more details! 

**All sales are final. No refunds.**

title: Covering Race and Ethnicity: A Guideline for Finding The Deeper Stories
description:
Covering Race and Ethnicity: A Practical Guideline to Finding the Deeper Stories


Join us for a special discussion on Race and Ethnicity moderated by Venise Wagner, journalism professor San Francisco State University and co-editor of "Reporting Inequity:Tools and Methods for Covering Race and Ethnicity.” 

Panelists include Alden Loury of WBEZ; Fernando Diaz of The Chicago Reporter; Teri Arvesu of Univision; and Jeff Kelly Lowenstein of Grand Valley State University.

Who should attend? Journalists, students and anyone who cares about telling the story of race & ethnicity in Chicago.

Sponsors include Public Narrative, National Association of Black Journalists - Chicago Chapter, The Chicago Headline Club, The Goodman Theatre and The Chicago Reporter.

title: Closing North American Skies - the People and Stories Behind "Come From Away"
description:
When tragedy hit the United States on September 11, 2001, decisions on what to do had to be made quickly. Lieutenant General Eric “Rick” Findley of the Royal Canadian Air Force was on watch as NORAD’s Director of Operations that day, overseeing both Canadian and U.S. personnel and North American air space at Cheyenne Mountain Operations Center. 
Captain Beverley Bass, American Airlines’ first female Captain, was en route from Paris to Dallas with 156 passengers plus crew. Join Lt. General Findley, Captain Bass, and castmember James Earl Jones II from Come From Away Broadway during their conversation with Canadian Consul General John Cruickshank about their experiences and decisions on that day and how those actions led to the hit musical “Come From Away”, opening in Chicago on July 30th. 

*This program is free but a reservation is required. Please arrive early to guarantee seating. Doors open at 5:30PM.

A very special thank you to our friends and partners -

title: VIP Seating for Chicago Immigrant Stories II: Finale
description:
In “Chicago Immigrant Stories”, CJP’s artistry of cross-genre collaborations melds with the musical culture of some of Chicago’s immigrant communities. The July performance is an orchestral culmination of a series of collaborations and workshops with musicians from Chicago’s Greek, Mexican, Bulgarian, and Argentinian communities.
Guest collaborators and featured artists include Grammy-nominated folk ensemble Sones de México; Greek saxophonist and composer Athanasios Zervas, and guitarist Petros Dragoumis; and resident CJP orchestra members - Argentinian pianist Leandro Lopez Varady and Bulgarian violinist Zara Zaharieva.

title: Off the Mound with Ryan Dempster to Benefit Special Olympics IL
description:
Former Cubs Pitcher Ryan Dempster to Host Live Show Benefitting Special Olympics Illinois
CHICAGO, IL. – Join Anthony Rizzo, Jeremy Roenick, Moises Alou, Jeff Garlin and more athletes and celebrities at Off the Mound with Ryan Dempster to benefit Special Olympics Illinois. The show is on Saturday July 20, 2019 at the Park West theater (322 W Armitage Ave, Chicago, IL) and will begin at 7:30pm.

Off the Mound with Ryan Dempster is a live, late-night style talk show hosted by former Chicago Cubs Pitcher Ryan Dempster featuring stories and laughs with MLB stars, past and present, and other great personalities from the sports and entertainment world! The show will also include appearances from Special Olympics Illinois athletes, fun games, and pre/post-show VIP opportunities.

Tickets go on sale on May 13, 2019 at 10:00am.

Visit www.offthemound.com to purchase tickets and learn more about the show!

title: Yolanda Kondonassis performs Ginastera’s Harp Concerto with Grant Park Orchestra
description: Internationally acclaimed harpist Yolanda Kondonassis performs Alberto Ginastera’s Harp Concerto as soloist with the Grant Park Orchestra led by Emmanuel Villaume at Jay Pritzker Pavilion. Since its premiere in 1965, Ginastera's Harp Concerto has acquired an almost cult status as the definitive harp concerto of the 20th century. With its pulsing Latin rhythms, virtuosic displays, and creative use of many unique colors and special effects, the work has received numerous performances during the past several decades, nearly 200 of which have been performed by Yolanda Kondonassis. The program also includes Ravel’s charming Mother Goose Suite and Bizet’s First Symphony. This concert will be broadcast live on 98.7WFMT and streamed live at www.wfmt.com.

title: Hope for Healing Benefit Concert
description: 21+ / www.joesbar.comThe Social Alcohol Band has teamed up with Hope for Healing for a summer fundraising concert. Hope for Healing is an organization that focuses on supporting individuals and communities affected by addiction through education and harm reduction efforts. This charity was founded by the Stefani family following the overdose death of Matt Stefani. Matt was good friends with the members of The Social Alcohol Band and loved watching them play while in college. The Social Alcohol Band plays a wide array of different styles of music ranging from Tom Petty to Lou Bega, The Jackson 5 to Weezer, Billy Joel to The Strokes, Dave Mathews Band to Zac Brown Band, and everything in between. The ticket price includes a 3 hour open bar and a hell of a lot of fun!

title: WBEZ's Podcast Passport Presents Wow in the World Pop Up Party
description:
WBEZ's Podcast Passport presents Wow in the World Pop up Party live at the Chicago Theatre. Join Guy Raz, Mindy Thomas and The Pop Ups (three-time Grammy nominees and creators of the "Wow in the World" theme song) for a highly interactive show that engages curious kids and their grown-ups in science, wonder, imagination, and music and leaves them all saying "WOW"!

Wow in the World is a podcast for curious kids and their grown-ups that leads listeners on a journey away from their screens, inside their brain, out into space, and deep into the coolest new stories in science, technology, and innovation.

The Pop Ups is a collaboration, between Brooklyn musicians Jason Rabinowitz and Jacob Stein, which have set the standard for children's music since 2010. Their most recent album, Giants of Science, won their third GRAMMY Nomination for Best Children's Album, a Parent's Choice Gold Award, and had two #1 singles on Sirius XM Radio.

title: Socialism 2019
description:
No Borders, No Bosses, No Binaries
In a moment of rising class struggle, resurgent social movements, and the growing popular appeal of socialism, the Socialism 2019 Conference will be an important gathering space for today’s left.
We're excited to announce that this year the conference will be sponsored by Haymarket Books and Jacobin. We hope that the conference will continue to bring together hundreds of activists from across the country for four days of organizing, learning, and collaboration.
Featuring dozens of panels, lectures, meet-ups, and workshops on topics like the fight against racism, how to win gender justice, radical working-class struggle, current debates on the left, and more, the Socialism Conference is an important contribution to the new socialist moment.
For information on speakers, schedules, and logistics, visit the Socialism Conference website.

title: Balkan Summer Sessions - Vol 1 at No.9 (PRYSM)
description:
We officially present you a new series of Balkan events that will make you summer a one to remember! Over the period of next few months we will reform the Balkan nightlife in Chicago as we take on a new challenge of delivering the most exclusive and sophisticated parties you have ever experienced. We start on July 3rd at No. 9 Chicago, which over the past year has hosted numerous entertainment celebrities. No.9 (Pronounced: Number Nine)— 9 for short is a play off of the iconic fragrance Chanel No.5— with a twist, there are 9 spacious candle lit tables. Paying homage to CoCo with two floor to ceiling images of mademoiselle herself mirrored on either side of the stunning (24) custom built steal bottle lockers. Upon entry stands a giant 9x9ft display / partition showcasing commissioned pieces of art by LEFTY, an up and coming street artist native to Chicago as well as magnum bottles of champagne. Join us for this unique event as we have numerous special hosts ready to party with you! title: The Music Man
description: Coming to Chicago's Goodman Theatre for Independence Week, the All-American classic The Music Man is a Tony-winning musical-comedy-romance that follows the adventures of fast-talking "Professor" Harold Hill. The charming con man plans to trick the good people of an Iowa town into buying instruments for a boys' band he has no intention of organizing, then marching off with their hard-earned cash. But there's trouble right there in River City when he becomes fond of the townspeople and falls for the lovely Marian the Librarian, even as she begins to see through his scheme. Mary Zimmerman (The Jungle Book, Wonderful Town) brings her magic touch to "one of the sunniest musicals ever" (The New York Times), including memorable favorites like "Goodnight My Someone," "Seventy-Six Trombones," "Gary, Indiana" and "Till There Was You."

title: WBEZ Chicago Presents Seven Things I’ve Learned: An Evening with Ira Glass
description:
Ira Glass returns to Chicago for an emotional and thought-provoking presentation of his captivating stage show Seven Things I’ve Learned, sponsored by Barnes & Thornburg LLP. Using audio clips, music and video, Ira will share the personal stories of Americans from all walks of life and deliver a unique talk on the lessons he’s learned during his career as a storyteller.

Ira Glass is the host and creator of the public radio program This American Life, heard each week by over 2.2 million listeners on more than 500 public radio stations, with another 2.5 million downloading each podcast. He’s also one of the editors of the podcasts Serial and S-Town.

During this presentation, Ira will mix stories live onstage, showcasing his creative process for the audience. Audience members will learn what inspires him to create, what drives the work he does and how success and failure has impacted his career and life decisions.

title: Devising Theatre - A 3-Day Sojourn Theatre Institute
description: DETAILS: 9AM-4:30PM June 22nd-24th, 2019 WORKSHOP LEADER: Sojourn Founding Artistic Director, Michael Rohd LOCATION: The Alice B. Rapoport Center for Education & Engagement, Goodman Theatre, Chicago Limited openings - all availability is on a first come, first serve basis. If registering before 11:59PM Central on April 12th, 2019, use code EARLYBIRD for discounted registration. Sojourn Theatre has been devising original work for almost twenty years. Documentary theatre about public education on the floor of a state legislature (Witness Our Schools); a site-specific adaptation of Brecht in a working Subaru dealership (Good); an interactive urban planning performance tackling gentrification at an international Arts Festival (BUILT); an immersive journey that brought urban and rural audiences across 50 miles to share a meal, conversation and a multi-generational tale of love and loss (On The Table); a participatory civic theatre event that engages strangers in the act of deciding how to spend real dollars on poverty reduction in their own community (How To End Poverty in 30 Minutes). We create gatherings that act like shows, processes that move like art, engagement that listens like relationship, and workshops that feel like discovery. Join Sojourn Theatre artistic director Michael Rohd alongside Sojourn ensemble members for three days of play, ideas, strategies and dialogue. Including explorations of movement and improvisation, facilitation and dramaturgy, generative activity and group practice, we will explore how to make work collaboratively that starts, grows, iterates and becomes. Sojourn and CPCP work to support and increase the capacity of artists and community organizations to imagine and collaborate towards racially equitable and economically just communities. This year we are able to offer a limited number of full and partial scholarships to offset tuition costs. If financial need is an obstacle to participation, please email sara@thecpcp.org for information on how to apply for a scholarship. People from historically underrepresented, underfunded, and excluded populations and communities are especially encouraged to apply. The scholarship application deadline has been extended to 11:59PM Central on March 29th, 2019. The Sojourn Theatre Summer Institute is hosted by The Alice B. Rapoport Center for Education and Engagement at Goodman Theatre as part of a multi year CPCP & Goodman Theatre partnership. Questions? Contact, Sara Sawicki at: sara@thecpcp.org Join us for our other 3-Day Institute this summer, Civic Practice, Creative Placemaking & Placekeeping: June 18th-20th, 2019. Or our one-day Intro to Civic Practice, Creative Placemaking & Placekeeping on June 18th, 2019. More info at www.thecpcp.org \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\ WORKSHOP LEADER BIO: MICHAEL ROHD Michael Rohd is founding artistic director of Sojourn Theatre. In 2015, he received an Otto Rene Castillo award for Political Theater and The Robert Gard Foundation Award for Excellence. He recently accepted a Professorship at Arizona State University's Herberger Institute for Design & Art, is author of the widely translated book Theatre for Community, Conflict, and Dialogue and leads the Center for Performance and Civic Practice. He was the 2013-2016 Doris Duke Artist-in-Residence at Lookingglass Theater Company in Chicago. Recent/Current projects include leading a two year Sojourn Artist-in-Residence collaboration with Catholic Charities USA poverty reduction sites around the US; collaborations with Steppenwolf Theater, Bush Foundation, Lincoln Center, Singapore Drama Educators Association and Americans for the Arts; and, working with theaters and universities around the country to mount locally specific projects based on Sojourn's model performance/engagement process/production How To End Poverty in 90 Minutes.

title: PIRILLO x IRIDIUM: FASHION SHOW [AT PRYSM]
description:
PIRILLO x IRIDIUM - FASHION SHOW 

FRIDAY, JUNE 21st  [9PM - 10PM]

DETAILS:  [For any  additional information regarding this event, please contact Mike Maduko (630-962-6668) or Paolo Zamora (630-673-9715)]
Join Iridium and Pirillo at their debut on PRYSM’s fashion runway as they feature a variety of their original designs and exclusive pieces! Enjoy the show as we accommodate you with live DJ’s, passed champagne, and exclusive pop up shops! 
Pirillo Swimwear showcases simple, high quality swimwear that emphasizes the natural beauty of your body. We believe in style and comfort that doesn’t break the bank, along with showing that a ‘bikini body’ is not a one-size fit. Available online at http://www.pirilloswim.com or in store at Generation Bliss in Lemont
Iridium 77, is a Chicago-based fashion company. We have been catering to the wearable needs for many men & women for over 11 years. Our brand believes in giving you a certain variety of feelings that many are unable to achieve from other brands. Come check us out, in person,  at our Block37 location at 108 N State St.


TICKET INFO: PRYSM Nightclub offers Express Entry to ticket holders before 11:30PM. Early Arrival is strongly suggested. 
DRESS CODE: Be fashion forward, keep it trendy, and look your best! We expect our guests to make an effort when visiting our venue on all occasions. In all instances the decision of the management team is final.Any exercise of discretion under this dress code shall be applied in a gender-neutral, nondiscriminatory manner, in accordance with all applicable law. All decisions are final.

title: TECHSPO Chicago 2019 Technology Expo (Internet ~ Mobile ~ AdTech ~ MarTech ~ SaaS)
description:
About TECHSPO Chicago 2019
WHERE BUSINESS, TECH AND INNOVATION COLLIDE IN CHICAGO!

TECHSPO Chicago is a 2-day technology expo taking place June 20 – 21, 2019 at the luxurious Hyatt Regency McCormick Place in Chicago, Illinois. TECHSPO Chicago brings together developers, brands, marketers, technology providers, designers, innovators and evangelists looking to set the pace in our advanced world of technology.
Exhibitors showcase the next generation of technology & innovation; including; Internet, Mobile, AdTech, MarTech & SaaS. Be prepared to be inspired, amazed and educated on how these evolving technologies will impact your business for the better.
As part of TECHSPO Chicago is a limited attendance paid event, DigiMarCon Midwest 2019 Digital Marketing Conference (https://digimarconmidwest.com). If the conference is where the learning, theory and inspiration happens, then the TECHSPO floor is where the testing, networking and product interaction takes place. 
Attendance is limited, Register today!

Venue
Hyatt Regency McCormick Place
2233 S Martin Luther King Dr, Chicago, IL 60616, United States



Step into the Hyatt Regency McCormick Place, where great things happen seamlessly. Conveniently connected to the McCormick Place Convention Center, this downtown Chicago hotel offers the ideal destination for you to work, relax and explore.  Enjoy the beautiful Lake Michigan backdrop and easy access to waterfront trails. Walk just outside of our doors to discover exciting Chicago attractions, like Soldier Field, Museum Campus, Millennium Park, and shopping on the Magnificent Mile. Hyatt Regency McCormick Place is a premier conference center venue where TECHSPO Chicago 2019 will be held.





TECHSPO Chicago 2019 will be held in the Regency Ballroom on the 2nd Floor.

title: CYSO Midsommar Celebration
description:
CYSO’s Symphony Orchestra kicks off their Tour of the Baltics with a free concert celebrating summer! Join our talented young musicians for this family-friendly performance. Before and after the concert, stick around for a festival featuring organizations, activities, and crafts from the countries the orchestra will visit on tour: Sweden, Finland, Estonia, and Russia. Festival runs from 2:00 – 6:00 pm. Concert begins at 3:00 pm.

CONCERT PROGRAM
CYSO’s Symphony Orchestra led by Music Director Allen Tinkham
George Walker | Address for Orchestra
Ottorino Respighi | Fountains of Rome
Jean Sibelius | Symphony no. 7 in C Major
Igor Stravinsky | The Firebird: Suite (1919)

FESTIVAL ACTIVITIES
SWEDEN | Make a Midsommar flower crown and viking hat with activities provided by the Swedish American Museum
ESTONIA | Cultural and historical information about the Estonian capital of Tallinn from Estonian Vice Consulate Siim Soot
FINLAND | Learn about Finnish music including composer Jean Sibelius and traditional Kantele music with Liisa McMahon of the Finnish American Society of the Midwest
RUSSIA | Design your own Russian matryoshka nesting doll and explore cultural and historical information coordinated by Roosevelt viola faculty, Igor Fedotov

From stillness + silence... to sweaty flow and blissful beats, with sound so rich you could touch it.





























On Friday, June 14th, Deep House Yoga, Yolie Yoga and Zacharias (Barry’s Bootcamp & Yoga 2.0) make their debut at Prysm Nightclub with a unique, inspiring, and playful class.

Come for the zen AND the groove -- you won't just hear the music -- you'll FEEL it in your heart and body, from start to finish.

title: The Union League Boys & Girls Clubs Toasts their Big Anniversary at 22nd Annual Wine Dinner
description:
The Union League Boys & Girls Clubs will celebrate their 22nd Annual Wine Dinner on June 14th at the Union League Club. This wine dinner benefits the over 14,000 youths associated with the Union League Boys & Girls Club. A special toast made in honor of the nonprofit’s 100th year anniversary. The event will feature the iconic Heitz Cellar wines which produces the highest quality wine since 1961. Guests are invited for a night of exquisite dining and wine pairings along with an exciting auction and more!

Guests will enjoy a five-course meal specially created by the renowned Union League Club's Chef Garbin with each course paired with a different Heitz Cellar wine. This years event will have Union League Boys & Girls Clubs Trustees, Lisa Shade and Michael L. Sullivan as co-chairs.

Individual tickets start at $225. To RSVP call 312-765-0405 or visit http://www.ulbgc.org/events. You must be 21 or over to attend. 

ABOUT THE UNION LEAGUE BOYS & GIRLS CLUBS 
Since 1919, the Union League Boys & Girls Clubs have been serving vulnerable youth in some of Chicago’s neediest neighborhoods. In 2017, the Union League Boys & Girls Clubs served over 14,000 youth members at seven well-equipped and professionally staffed inner-city Clubs that bring effective after-school programming to youth in the Pilsen, West Town, Humboldt Park, Bucktown, South Lawndale and Englewood communities.  The Union League Boys & Girls Clubs is a separate organization from the Boys & Girls Clubs of Chicago; both are chartered by the Boys & Girls Clubs of America. The Union League Boys & Girls Clubs also serves Court-detained youth assigned to Juvenile Temporary Detention Program to reduce recidivism. The nonprofit staffs and manages its own 250-acre summer camp in southern Wisconsin where Club youth have a chance to enjoy supervised outdoor activities not easily accessible in an urban environment, as well as continue to develop healthy peer and adult relationships. For more information, to get involved or volunteer, please visit www.ulbgc.org.

title: Transport Chicago Conference 2019
description: Transport Chicago is an annual conference that provides a forum for the exchange of knowledge in transportation research, policies, and practice. The Conference, first held in 1986, explores a broad range of transportation modes and issues. This event regularly attracts over 300 academics and professionals from the Chicago region and beyond, offering an excellent opportunity for the transportation community to make connections and share experiences. Transport Chicago includes breakout learning sessions where attendees can learn about the latest trends, research, and emerging technology in the transportation field. Admission also includes continental breakfast, lunch, and snacks and refreshments at a networking session. Learn more at www.transportchicago.org or email registration@transportchicago.org

title: OUT OF SIGHT Chicago 2019 Orientation
description:
Thank you for joining in on a summer of self-discovery and empowerment through OUT OF SIGHT this Summer!
 
We look forward to working with you to create meaningful experiences for participants, across all ages and dedicated teen camps in neighborhoods throughout Chicago.


Last year, Chicago welcomed Lawrence Weiner’s OUT OF SIGHT, a participatory floor installation (modeled after a hopscotch) that invites active participation and encourages audiences to consider the direction of their lives. This project was inspired by the concepts: 
 
Exuberance   Energy   Happiness   Vision   Visualization   
Enlightenment   Spontaneity   Serendipity 

In 2019 large scale installations of the marelle (French for hopscotch) are open to the public at the following parks:

Eugene Field Park  (Albany Park)
Hamilton Park Cultural Center (Engelwood)
Julia de Burgos Park (Humboldt Park/Logan Square)
La Villita Park (Little Village/South Lawndale)
Maggie Daley Park (the Loop)
Ping Tom Memorial Park (Chinatown) 

We welcome you to participate in the OUT OF SIGHT Chicago 2019 Orientation as we build our summer together. You will have the opportunity to:


Meet the OUT OF SIGHT team and learn more about the vision
Park Supervisors discuss their communities and the teen camper interests
Teaching Artists sharing their talents and build out weekly activities
Motivational Edge Miami's founders speak about creating OUT OF SIGHT programming for youth

We are thrilled to have you joining in on this year of discovery and play. Please RSVP by this Saturday, June 8th.

description:
Grgich Hills Estate is an iconic Napa Valley Winery, consistently producing wines of the highest quality for the past 40 years. Committed to natural winegrowing and sustainability, Grgich Hills Estate farm their five certified organic estate vineyards without artificial pesticides or herbicides, rely on wild yeast fermentation and use their passion and art to handcraft food-friendly, balanced and elegant wines. 

Guests will enjoy a five-course meal specially created by the renowned Union League Club's Chef Garbin with each course paired with a different Grgich wine. 

Sean Barrett, National Sales Ambassador from Grgich Hills Estate, will be the wine host and guest speaker.

title: A&A; Ballet Open Auditions for “The Art Deco Nutcracker”
description:
Audition attire: Girls-black camisole leotard, pink footed tights, pink canvas ballet and pointe shoes (age/level appropriate); Boys-black footed tights, white tight fitted t-shirt, black ballet shoes. The audition will include some basic dance movement and a combination to be performed in character. No preparation of audition material is necessary. Dancers will be notified via email within the week after the audition if they have been cast. A production fee will be required for dancers performing “The Art Deco Nutcracker” and varies depending on role. Rehearsals begin in September and will take place primarily on Saturdays at the American Rhythm Center. A pre-registration form may be downloaded at aacenterfordance.org. 

Set in 1920s America, Kremnev's “The Art Deco Nutcracker,” featuring Tchaikovsky’s beloved score, is a fresh, yet traditional take on the beloved holiday favorite. “The Art Deco Nutcracker” is Kremnev's eighth full-length ballet. His work has been presented at the world-renowned Bolshoi Theatre in Moscow, Lincoln Center in New York, and the Opernhaus Zurich in Switzerland, among other prestigious venues across the globe. Tickets for Kremnev's “The Art Deco Nutcracker” go on sale at a later date to be announced.

description:
The Midwest Real Estate Networking Summit will deliver unique content and actionable steps for attendees to prosper through their real estate investments. We will cater to the specific needs of investors so the experience is catered to their area of focus.
The intent of this conference is to help attendees take the next step and do their next deal, especially those looking to invest in the Midwest. Whether an attendee is a complete newbie or an experienced syndicator, we want to provide the tips, strategies and networking opportunities to help attendees grow their portfolio.

title: Memorial Day Weekend Booze Cruises on Lake Michigan
description:
Memorial Day Weekend Booze Cruises on Lake Michigan

Tickets include a live DJ, dancing, giveaways and the best views of Chicago! Chicago may be the Second City, but our booze cruises are first class! Cruising aboard a three-story, 140-foot, luxury yacht, you’ll enjoy breathtaking views of Chicago’s iconic landmarks from Lake Michigan. Take in the sights from either of the climate-controlled interior decks, or enjoy the breeze on the open top deck. Be sure to take a spin on the dance floor as the DJ plays your favorite Top 40, hip-hop, and party hits. Don’t forget to grab a drink from any of our full bars! Take advantage of Chicago’s best asset and come aboard the cruise!

title: Chicago Philharmonic & Cirque de la Symphonie
description:
Clowns, acrobats, contortionists and jugglers join the virtuosic musicians of the Chicago Philharmonic in an extraordinary spectacle for the eyes and ears at Harris Theater. Strongmen and aerialists perform superhuman feats onstage alongside the orchestra, perfectly choreographed to classic cinematic scores, in this spectacular family-friendly season finale. 

Cirque de la Symphonie is an exciting production designed to bring the magic of cirque to the music hall. For more than 10 years, it has thrilled veteran concert goers and new patrons as they see accomplished aerial flyers, acrobats, contortionists, dancers, jugglers, balancers, and strongmen perform to live symphony music. Classical masterpieces and film score favorites including selections from West Side Story, Superman, Star Wars, Harry Potter and more will dazzle audiences of all ages!

title: Paint the Town Red: Concert Ft. Chicago Children’s Choir & Hamilton Company
description:
Taking the stage at the Paint the Town Red concert will be 5,000 students from Chicago Children’s Choir (CCC), the nation’s preeminent youth choral organization. They will be joined by cast members from the Hamilton Chicago Company to perform a selection of songs from the Tony award-winning musical.
Paint the Town Red is an annual free concert that marks the end of the student’s choral season and serves as a celebration of the positive impact of the Chicago Children’s Choir by showcasing the powerful voices of Chicago’s youth.

title: Bellavita Chicago 2019 - The Italian F&B Show | VIP Judge Pass
description:
Running for the fourth year in a row, Bellavita Expo takes place at the National Restaurant Association Show, Lakeside Center, May 18-21.
Visit Bellavita to discover a wide range of Italian food and beverages and apply here to vote for the best product of the show!
VIP Judges can decide to visit the Bellavita Italian pavilion on any day and at any time within the following judging opening times:


SATURDAY, MAY 18  from 10:00 a.m. to 5:00 p.m.


SUNDAY, MAY 19  from 10:00 a.m. to 5:00 p.m.


MONDAY, MAY 20  from 10:00 a.m. to 5:00 p.m.



As a VIP Judge, you will get to taste authentic Italian delicacies, connect with a whole new group of suppliers, and award those exhibitors who have earned the top spot.
Did you know? Bellavita VIP Judges have priority seating for all the cooking demos, wine tastings and industry panels at the Bellavita Food & Wine Academy! Click here to see the full schedule.
Professionals eligible to attend the National Restaurant Association Show may obtain a Bellavita VIP Judge pass. We reserve the right to amend this list based on the criteria required to attend the trade show. Specifically, attendance will not be granted to anyone who does not clearly state their job role within the F&B industry.
All the F&B professionals who will make the selection process can get free entry for the 2019 National Restaurant Association Show upon request. The result of your application will be emailed to you before May 18.To learn more, contact Bellavita Awards Director Enrico Longobucco at elongobucco@quirismedia.com

title: The Miracle of the West with Jonah Goldberg
description:
Join Illinois Policy Institute, National Review Institute, and the Chicago chapter of America's Future Foundation on Tuesday, May 14, as we welcome NRI Fellow Jonah Goldberg for "The Miracle of the West."
Jonah and Illinois Policy Institute CEO John Tillman will discuss the values that lifted humanity out of a 250,000-year cycle of poverty, hunger, and war and into prosperity, and how our current cultural and political moment is turning those values into vices. The conversation will explore how the miracle of modernity was created, how we're losing it - and what can be done to renew it.
Jonah Goldberg is a senior editor of National Review, a fellow at National Review Institute, and a fellow at American Enterprise Institute. He's the author of three New York Times bestsellers, including his most recent book, Suicide of the West.
Please note: the Union League Club adheres to a no denim or athletic wear dress code.

Margaret Trudeau, Mother of PM Justin Trudeau

Celebrate Mother’s Day with the mom of a world leader! In a world premier appearance, Margaret Trudeau, mother of Canadian Prime Minister, Justin Trudeau, is coming to Chicago. Her intimate performance, Certain Woman of an Age will be staged exclusively at UP Comedy Club at the Second City. title: Food for Thought: Connections Between Nutrition and Brain Health
description:
There is growing research evidence that what you eat can affect your mental health, including your mood and cognition. The evidence supporting nutrition’s role in brain health will be discussed in our next Science in the Parks program.
Specifically, Dr. Tussing-Humphreys will focus on discussing research tying a Western-type diet pattern to mental health disorders such as depression and dementia. She will also review how a plant-based diet like the Mediterranean diet can be beneficial to mood and cognitive health.  
Speaker:
Lisa Tussing-Humphreys, PhD

Dr. Tussing-Humphreys is Assistant Professor in the Division of Academic Internal Medicine and Geriatrics of the Department of Medicine in the University of Illinois at Chicago College of Medicine. She directs the UI Cancer Center's Diet and Behavior Shared Resource and is an associate in the UIC Building Interdisciplinary Research Careers in Women’s Health and an IHRP Fellow. Her current work focuses on obesity-associated iron metabolism dysfunction and its relationship to health status and disease risk.
A registered dietitian, Dr. Tussing-Humphreys earned her doctoral degree in human nutrition from the UIC College of Applied Health Sciences in 2009, writing her dissertation on hepcidin-mediated iron deficiency of obesity. She holds an MS in nutritional sciences from the University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign and a BS in clinical dietetics from SUNY College at Buffalo. Before returning to UIC in 2012, Dr. Tussing-Humphreys was research scientist with the USDA Agricultural Research Service, and principal investigator of a church-based diet and physical activity intervention for African American adults in the Lower Mississippi Delta region.
Event Details:
Thursday, May 9th, 2019 from 6:00 pm to 7:30 pm, Ping Tom Memorial Park, Leonard M. Louie Fieldhouse, 1700 South Wentworth Avenue, Chicago, IL 60616.
This event is free to attend and seating will be first come, first served. 
This program is a part of the Science in the Parks and We Move Chicago initiatives.
  
 
Parking and Transportation:
Ping Tom Park is easily accessible by CTA Red Line Trains at the Cermak-Chinatown stop. For detailed travel information visit www.transitchicago.com or call the Travel Information Center at 1-888-YOUR-CTA or 1-888-CTA-TTY1 (TTY).

title: CLO Breakfast Club - Chicago 2019
description:
Faster, Better, Smarter: Creating a Future Ready Workforce
Making predictions is always a gamble. But there’s no risk in forecasting the need for a faster, better, smarter workforce. The sheer pace of technology and competitive innovation alone assures an unrelenting need to up-skill.
But employees aren’t the only ones facing a future where what drives performance today is likely to become irrelevant or obsolete tomorrow. Learning executives also feel intense pressure to constantly improve, reinvent and retool their enterprise education initiatives to be faster, better, smarter, too.
Join us at the CLO Breakfast Club where we’ll be discussing the trends, technologies and practices transforming employee development into an even more powerful force for sustained success.
For more information, including the agenda and speakers, please visit: chicago.clobreakfastclub.com
We look forward to seeing you there!

Success. The 78. Big Trends to Watch.
Curt Bailey knows what it takes to complete legendary deals. With more than 25 years of experience and numerous catalytic projects behind him, Curt and Related Midwest have helped re-define and re-shape the city of Chicago.
But his biggest project yet is looming: The 78
Come hear Curt discuss the future of Chicago via the future of The 78, the nuances that lead to game-changing success in this industry, and the top three tends he's watching as he looks toward the end of 2019.

title: MADE - A Brand New Mother’s Day Art Market
description:
MADE, a one-day art market just in time for Mother’s Day! MADE, a carefully curated experience, features the newest, quirkiest, and most interesting hand-made pieces all created by passionate "makers" from Chicagoland and beyond. 

From art to food, clothing to lotions, jewelry to home décor, everything at the show is made by hand by the people who love making them. This indoor shopping and buying event, which features one-of-a-kind and super unique Mother’s Day gifts, will be held at Chicago’s Morgan Manufacturing in the West Loop (401 N. Morgan Street) on Sunday, May 5th from 11 am to 5 pm. Admission is FREE! 

The first 100 people through the doors will receive a $5 MADE voucher to spend as they wish on any artist purchase, as well as $1 off the Mother’s Day MADE specialty drinks: “Mom”osas and “Ma”tinis! Artists from Blick Art Supplies will be on site hosting two FREE Mother’s Day art projects for all to enjoy including create your own Mother’s Day flowers bouquets and make your own Mother’s Day cards. Judy’s Pizza will be serving food for purchase throughout the show. For more information, please visit www.AmdurProductions.com.

description:
Cursed by a wicked fairy, the newborn Princess Aurora is fated to die from a prick to her finger on her sixteenth birthday. A good fairy intervenes to alter the wicked fairy’s tragic spell: instead of dying, Princess Aurora and her entire kingdom, will fall into a deep sleep. Only true love’s kiss will unleash the power to awaken her and the rest of her kingdom. 

The production is choreographed by Kremnev and Reznik and features Tchaikovsky’s beloved score. title: 17th Annual CHIRP Record Fair & Other Delights
description:
NOTE: WHILE ADVANCE SALES HAVE ENDED, TICKETS ARE AVAILABLE FOR CASH PURCHASE ON SITE.
It's the 17th year of the CHIRP Record Fair! Join us at Plumbers Hall to dig through thousands of crates of vinyl records, as well as DVDs, CDs, posters, and more. It's a music collector's paradise! We've got over 100 tables of vinyl this year - our biggest yet! And you can even get a sneak peek at the records we'll be slinging at the CHIRP records table, to prep for your early admission shopping!
In addition, our lower level will be filled with great food, beer, live music, and multiple Other Delights!

Gear Showcase on the lower level!
Kid's activities up in The Nest, with special programming from the Chicago Children's Museum!
Live music from OVEF OW, The Jellies, Baby Money (solo), DPCD, Thair, and Charming Hokum (Bob Gerics & Megan Donahue)!
Live music and comedy from Groovebox!
Special performances by the Blue Ribbon Glee Club and Reggio the Hoofer!
DJ sets from Van Paugam, Miss Alex White, DJ Chuck Wren, & Metro Chicago founder Joe Shanahan!
Food from Conscious Plates and Taco in a Bag - vegetarian options available!
Beer from Half Acre! Cider from Eris! Mezzo Spritz canned cocktails from Virtue! Wine provided by In Fine Spirits!
Coffee from Metropolis!
First 500 attendees get a free tote bag with download code for the CHIRP Record Fair Local Label Sampler!
Bike valet available, courtesy of West Town Bikes!

Early Admission ($25) begins at 8am and allows readmission all day long. General Admission ($8) begins at 10am. 
The CHIRP Record Fair & Other Delights is sponsored by Discogs!
The CHIRP Record Fair & Other Delights is a benefit for CHIRP Radio. Listen online at chirpradio.org or at 107.1FM on the north side of Chicago!
This year's poster (available through advanced ticket purchase for a discount!) was created by CHIRP's own Annabelle Goldin-Mertdogan!


FAQs
Will tickets be sold at the door?
Yes, though you should know - at-the-door sales are cash-only (ATMs on site), and the ticket lines are quite long in the morning. Buying an advanced ticket will let you beat the rush!
Are there ID requirements or an age limit to enter the event?
Nope! This is an all-ages event. However, we will be checking IDs for beer ticket sales and when said beer tickets are exchanged for drinks. Children under 12 are admitted free with a paying adult.
Are pets allowed?
No, no pets are allowed in Plumbers Hall.
What are my transport/parking options getting to the event?
The Plumbers Hall has a large parking lot surrounding the building, with plenty of spaces. We will also have a bike valet available for cyclists - courtesy of West Town Bikes!
From the Eisenhower (I-290), take exit 28B toward Paulina/Ashland. Head north on Paulina, turn right onto Ogden Ave, then right again onto Washington Blvd - we'll be on the left.
From the Kennedy (I-90/I-94 north of the Loop), take exit 50A toward Ogden Ave. Turn right onto Ogden and head south. Turn left onto Washington Blvd - we'll be on the left.
From the Stevenson (I-55), take exit 290 for Damen. Keep left at the fork to head north on S Damen Ave. After about 2 miles, turn right onto W Ogden Ave, then turn right onto Washington Blvd - we'll be on the left.
From the Dan Ryan (I-90/I-94 south of the Loop), head north past I-55 and exit onto I-290. After a mile, take exit 28B toward Paulina/Ashland. Turn right to head north on Ashland, turn right onto Ogden Ave, then right again onto Washington Blvd - we'll be on the left.
We are also located near the Ashland station on the Green & Pink 'L' lines, as well as the #9, #X9, and #20 buses. We are just over a mile west of the Ogilvie and Union Metra stations, and a little less than two miles east of the Western Ave Metra MD-N, MD-W, and NCS line station.
Do I have to bring my printed ticket to the event?
Nope! We'll be able to check you in with your digital ticket on your mobile device, or with your name. 
What is the refund policy?
All sales are final. If you cannot attend, a friend or family member may claim your ticket in your name on the day of the fair.
The name on the registration/ticket doesn't match the attendee. Is that okay?
Yes, as long as you can provide the name of the attendee that the ticket was purchased under.

National Achievers Congress Chicago 2019 - Keynote speaker Tony Robbins, special guest speaker Gary Vaynerchuk, Shark Tank's Kevin O'Leary, and many more will take the stage for this immersive mega event, bringing some of the world’s most recognizable sales experts, investors, performance specialists and entrepreneurs to one stage.
Here's what you'll learn in just one day:

Real-life tools and strategies used by industry-leading experts
How to go from where you are to where you want to go
Powerful exercises to shift mindset and overcome self-doubt
How to shed limiting beliefs and subconscious blocks
Practical and proven ways to raise capital to fund a business
How to build confidence and resilience for a prosperous life

Receive live training on sales and marketing, business, investing, personal-development, and motivation from these super-star speakers:

TONY ROBBINS: #1 Business and Life Strategist
GARY VAYNERCHUK: CEO of VaynerMedia, Entrepreneur and Investor
KEVIN O'LEARY: Businessman, Entrepreneur, and Shark Tank Investor
JOSEPH MCCLENDON: The most sought after Ultimate Performance Specialist
DEAN GRAZIOSI: New York Times best-selling author, real estate investor
LOREN LAHAV: Momtrepreneur, Healthy Living Hottie, Goddess of GOYA
More guest speakers to be announced

You will join inspiring, world-leading, homegrown and international game-changers, who'll share the systems they used to turn their own passion into success. 
Learn from those playing at the top of their game!

National Achievers Congress: The Ultimate Wealth and Achievement Summit is a One day mega-event of top strategies for success in 2019 featuring proven successful leaders.  Personal and professional success begins by taking action and all successful people share one powerful characteristic: hunger.  The hunger to seek out knowledge through the most effective resources.  Our speakers began their journey from the bottom of the mountain and now they want to share the top of the mountain with you by sharing their experience and knowledge. 
The Ultimate Wealth and Achievement Summit has brought together a lineup of the best speakers that will share how to succeed in all areas of your life including: motivation, personal development, lifestyle, relationships, business, wealth and so much more! 
You will not want to miss the most impactful wealth and achievement seminar you will ever attend.
 
FAQs
What is the difference between the seating sections?
The more you pay the closer to the stage you will sit with less people in front of you.  Seats are not assigned, they are first come first served for each seating section.  
What's the refund policy?
There are no refunds but all tickets are fully transferable.
When will I receive my ticket?
You will recieve you ticket from the National Achievers Congress within 72 hours before the event..
 Do I have to bring my printed ticket to the event?
A printed ticket will help you through the registration process more rapidly.  If you choose to show your ticket on your phone, we ask that you have it ready when you arrive at the registration tables.
Is my ticket transferrable?
Yes your ticket is fully transferrable. 
 Is it ok if the name on my ticket or registration doesn't match the person who attends?
Yes it is ok if the name on your ticket does not match the person attending.

title: Ring Lardner Awards for Excellence in Sports Journalism  Benefits Union League Boys & Girls Clubs
description:
The 14th Awards for Excellence in Sports Journalism event to benefit the work of the Union League Boys & Girls Clubs will be held on April 18th at the Union League Club. This award ceremony honors the very best in sports journalism in Ring Lardner’s legacy with this year even more special because of the Union League Boys & Girls Clubs 100 year anniversary. The Ring Lardner Awards honors broadcasters and writers who exemplify the wit and warmth of Ring Lardner’s writing.

Guests of this special awards ceremony will enjoy a cocktail reception with a silent auction and a wine basket raffle, dinner followed by the program. This year’s Ring Lardner committee includes George Maragos and Paul Shade as Co-Chairs , Chris Bohus, Susan Prather, Terry Hendrickson, Ken Nordine, Jim Lynch, Greg Schiller, Rich Gatto and Chris Robling. 

The Union League Boys & Girls Clubs is a separate organization than the Boys & Girls Clubs of Chicago.  Both are chartered by the Boys & Girls Clubs of America. For more information on the nonprofit, please visit  www.ulbgc.org.

ABOUT THE UNION LEAGUE BOYS & GIRLS CLUBS 
Since 1919, the Union League Boys & Girls Clubs have been serving vulnerable youth in some of Chicago’s neediest neighborhoods. In 2017, the Union League Boys & Girls Clubs served over 14,000 youth members at seven well-equipped and professionally staffed inner-city Clubs that bring effective after-school programming to youth in the Pilsen, West Town, Humboldt Park, Bucktown, South Lawndale and Englewood communities.  The Union League Boys & Girls Clubs is a separate organization from the Boys & Girls Clubs of Chicago; both are chartered by the Boys & Girls Clubs of America. The Union League Boys & Girls Clubs also serves Court-detained youth assigned to Juvenile Temporary Detention Program to reduce recidivism.  The nonprofit staffs and manages its own 250-acre summer camp in southern Wisconsin where Club youth have a chance to enjoy supervised outdoor activities not easily accessible in an urban environment, as well as continue to develop healthy peer and adult relationships. For more information, to get involved or volunteer, please visit www.ulbgc.org.

description:
VIVID 2019: A Celebration of Jazz

Tuesday, April 16 – 7:30 p.m.

Auditorium Theatre at Roosevelt University

50 E. Ida B. Wells Dr, Chicago, IL 60605

Free Performance

https://www.auditoriumtheatre.org/shows/vivid-2019/

 

Roosevelt University’s VIVID 2019 showcases performances by students and faculty (Victor Garcia, trumpet; Alejandro Cortés, piano; and Rubén Alvarez, percussion) from the Music Conservatory’s Jazz and Contemporary Music Program. CCPA Dean Emeritus Henry Fogel will be honored with the first CCPA Distinguished Achievement in the Arts Award. VIVID is a free event, but tickets are required. Tickets available to reserve through the Auditorium Theatre Box Office.

title: Louis York & The Shindellas #LoveTakeOverTour
description:
Coined one of the most electric performances by the Recording Academy (GRAMMYs) for their live set during the 2018 ESSENCE Festival, the Louis York and The Shindellas live show is a magnetic experience that redefines an expression of freedom through the arts and music.  Behind some of the biggest names and biggest songs of the last decade from Bruno Mars, Michael and Janet Jackson, Celine Dion, Ne-Yo, Rihanna, Toni Braxton, Whitney Houston, and many more, GRAMMY nominated songwriter and producer Claude Kelly and Chuck Harmony of the progressive band Louis York have crafted an unforgettable night of original musical works.  Its a genre bending, colorful, all inclusive experience that brings together an entire community.

Get tickets for yourself, someone special, and even the whole family today!
#LoveTakeOverTour

title: The 9th Annual Chicago Lighthouse Jazz Night
description:
Featuring Lisa Hilton/pianist and Nikki George/vocals
The award-winning composer and acclaimed pianist Lisa K. Hilton’s kaleidoscopic trans-genre and poly-generational style is once again topping play charts with her latest album, ESCAPISM. A former music school drop – out, she’s now captivating audiences in live performances and recording with some of today’s greatest living jazz musicians while toting a hefty catalog of 20 albums and 200 iTunes (mostly original) tracks. Hilton has performed at venues across the US from the legendary Carnegie Hall to the historic Green Mill in Chicago and is known for her warmth and storytelling on stage, as well as her expressive technique at the piano.  “One of the finest composers working in Jazz today.” Jazz Notes
With an ingratiating personality and amazing voice, Nikki George embodies the versatility of jazz.  She began her musical career in Chicago and has performed in New York, Florida, and Europe.   Her work has aired on Chicago stations, like WRRG and WNUA, and she has also appeared on WGN and WYIN television.  The Chicago Tribune had the following praise for Nikki George:  “sensational, electrifying…and an obviously accomplished singer.”

Jane Glover serves up a rich brew of Bach and Haydn, including Bach’s delightfully whimsical Coffee Cantata with soprano Joélle Harvey and energetic Orchestral Suite No. 2. Two symphonies by Haydn—the crackling Fire and the contemplative Philosopher—add a dash of Classical flavor.

MONDAY, April 1, 2019 7:30 PM
Harris Theater, Chicago
205 E. Randolph


Music of the Baroque Orchestra
Jane Glover, conductor
Joélle Harvey, soprano
Josh Lovell, tenor
Neal Davies, baritone

HAYDN
Symphony No. 59 in A Major (Fire)
BACH
Orchestral Suite No. 2
HAYDN
Symphony No. 22 in E-flat Major (The Philosopher)
BACH
Coffee Cantata

title: Giordano Dance Chicago Spring Series
description:
Giordano Dance Chicago Spring Series

With its Spring Series, Giordano Dance Chicago brings life-changing inspiration to Chicago and to the Harris Theater stage. This show features the world premiere of Flickers by award-winning choreographer Marinda Davis. Among her numerous accomplishments, Marinda has been named as a “Top 10 Young American Choreographer 25 & Under” by DanceTeacher magazine, and has set works for Dancing with the Stars and NBC’s World of Dance. The performance will also include Brock Clawson’s Sneaky Pete (2016), Prey by Ron De Jesus (2003), Autumn Eckman’s commonthread (2009) and the return of Ray Leeper’s SOUL (2018), which premiered at the Fall Performance Series last October.

title: Concert Three: Messiaen's Quartet for the End of Time (Chicago)
description:
PROGRAM
Antonio Vivaldi | Concerto in D Major, RV 84   (flute/violin/cello)Seth Boustead | Three for Zhou B  (flute/clarinet/violin/cello)Olivier Messiaen | Quartet for the End of Time   (clarinet/violin/cello/piano)
PICOSA ARTISTS
Jennie Oh Brown | fluteAndrea R. DiOrio | clarinetElizabeth Brausa Brathwaite | violinPaula Kosower | celloKuang-Hao Huang | pianoJonathon Kirk | Composer-in-Residence
Quartet for the End of Time was written while Messaien was held in a prisoner of war camp in Germany, now in Poland, during World War II.  Fellow prisoners premiered the quartet outside in the freezing rain on January 15, 1941. The title of the work "The End of Time" not only refers to a representation of the apocalypse, but also musically to an end to traditional concepts of time.  Messaien was a contemporary French composer who drew inspiration not only from his connection to the Paris Conservatory and his life as a noted contemporary composer, but also from non-western influences from Japan and Indonesian Gamelan, and perhaps most notably in nature itself through birdsongs.
Introducing this epic quartet on the program are two contrasting works.  Vivaldi's Concerto in D Major, RV 84 is a light and charming baroque work that will be performed in a modern context on flute, violin, cello, and piano.  Chicago composer Seth Boustead's Three for Zhou B for flute, clarinet, violin, and cello will be performed with artwork displayed by celebrated contemporary Chinese-American artists the Zhou brothers, ShanZuo and DaHuang Zhou. Join us for this eclectic program that explores the light with the dark and everything in between.

The parade marches north from Balbo Drive to Monroe Street, with a viewing stand situated in front of Buckingham Fountain.

title: Yacht Party Chicago's Unofficial St. Patrick's Day Booze Cruise
description:
Luxury Saturday Booze Cruise on Lake Michigan

Celebrate unofficial St. Patrick's Day with a mini getaway cruise on Lake Michigan. Catch breathtaking views of the Chicago skyline as you dance with friends on three floors of the Anita Dee II luxury yacht. With a live DJ and dancing, it's an action-packed afternoon of nothing but fun. title: 2019 Metro Advancement Council Luncheon
description:
ELIZABETH “BETSY” ZIEGLER KEYNOTE SPEAKER AND FIRST FEMALE CEO OF 1871, NOW THE NUMBER 1 UNIVERSITY AFFILIATED TECH INCUBATOR IN THE WORLD.
Previous to 1871, Betsy was the Chief Innovation Officer at the Kellogg School of Management, Northwestern University, responsible for portfolio innovation as well as integrating technology into the Kellogg educational experience. From 2011 through September 2015, she served as associate dean of degree programs and dean of students.
Prior to Kellogg, she served as a principal in McKinsey & Company’s Chicago office where she led the firm’s Life Insurance Operations and Technology practice and co-led its Financial Institutions Operations and Technology practice.
Ziegler holds an M.B.A. from Harvard Business School and received a B.A. in economics from The Ohio State University, where she graduated with distinction. She is also is a member of Ann & Robert H. Lurie Children’s Hospital of Chicago and the Museum of Science & Industry Board of Directors and an advisor and investor in many young technology companies.

title: 2019 Day & Night of the Living Ales
description: ***** EVENING SESSION NOW 25% OFF! ***** The national drink of Great Britain, cask conditioned ales have been served for centuries. Before brewers fell in love with artificial carbonation and filtering, beer was naturally conditioned by yeast in the cask, and served at a temperature warm enough to actually taste the beer. A properly served cask ale is neither cloudy, flat, nor warm; rather it is bright, with a gentle carbonation, and served at cellar temperature. Sample a vast array of different beers at our walk-around tasting featuring the best cask conditioned ales from Chicagoland breweries and specially selected guests. Food will be available for purchase. Casks are handled by the Chicago Beer Society's own experienced cellarmen, trained in the UK to care for and serve real ale. Attendees will vote on their favorites to crown The Champion Real Ales of Chicagoland for 2019! Admission includes souvenir tasting glass, program & beer samples. All ticket sales and sessions chosen are final. All beers will be available for both the afternoon and evening sessions. FEATURING CASK ALES FROM THESE PARTICIPATING BREWERIES: (full Beer list here: https://bit.ly/2tGbbmV) All Rise Brewing Co. Alter Brewing Co. Church Street Brewing Co. Empirical Brewery Finch Beer Co. Goose Island Beer Co. Goose Island Clybourn Brewhouse Hailstorm Brewing Co. Half Acre Beer Co. Haymarket Pub & Brewery Hopvine Brewing Co. Illuminated Brew Works Imperial Oak Brewing Co. Lakefront Brewery Maplewood Brewery & Distillery Metropolitan Brewing Mickey Finn's Brewery Middle Brow Beer Co. Noon Whistle Brewing Off Color Brewing Co. Open Outcry Brewing Co. Pig Minds Brewing Co. Prairie Street Brewing Co. Revolution Brewing Rock Bottom Orland Park Sketchbook Brewing Co. Spiteful Brewing Temperance Beer Company Tighthead Brewing Co. Two Brothers Artisan Brewing Twisted Hippo Urban Renewal Brewery *Note that sometimes beer gets spilled. Brewery participation is subject to change based on factors beyond our control.

description:
This job fair is being hosted by the consortium schools of University of Illinois at Chicago (UIC), Loyola University, and DePaul University. The fair will showcase employers representing private schools, public school districts, charter schools, and various non-profit organizations located throughout the city of Chicago, suburban locations, and other states (Wisconsin, Michigan, Colorado, Florida, and others).
Employers are seeking candidates who are education, social work, and other majors interested in working in education settings.
This Fair is open to the public and FREE! Bring plenty of resumes!

title: "The Scarlet Ibis"
description:
The Scarlet Ibis

The Scarlet Ibis is a moving tale about brotherhood, nature and family. Doodle is different, and his Brother knows it. With the school year looming on the horizon, Brother decides it’s time to make Doodle just like all the other kids. As they run, jump, play, and row through the woods of North Carolina, a storm approaches that will change the lives of both boys forever. Called “an outstanding new chamber opera … a moving, intense, and dignified creation” by The New York Times, The Scarlet Ibis asks why we other those who are different from us, and what exactly it means to be “normal.”

title: DARKSIDE
description:
Throwing down at Emporium Arcade Bar to celebrate our 7th year bringing dark beer, arcade and metal.

Last Sunday in February, the 24th, starting at Noon. We're lining up some killer offerings, new and some returning favorites.

This event was originally conceived as a way for craft beer drinkers, new and veteran, to explore dark beer. There are a lot of misconceptions about dark beer, and it's not always easy to reach for a 6 pack that you're not sure about. Darkside allows you to sample and explore some of the best dark beers on the market, some of which you may never see again!

TICKETS:Online Pre-Sale: $30Door: $40 (if we don't sell out)

WHAT YOU GET• A bag of game tokens• 8 samples (about 40 oz) of the beers available. You have the option to purchase full pours of any of your favorites as well.

title: Winter Tequila Festival
description:
Winter Tequila Tasting Festival

Whether you prefer it neat, as a shot with lime or mixed into a margarita, tequila reigns as one of Mexico's most famous exports. Now you can embrace the more subtle complexities of this storied beverage at this intimate two-hour tasting event at the Trophy Room in Chicago. Sample several varieties of "the devil's elixir" with 15 included tasting tickets, and enjoy food and drink specials. VIP admission gets you in 30 minutes before the crowd.

title: FRIENDS! The Musical Parody
description:
EVENT DESCRIPTION:
FRIENDS! The Musical Parody is the comedic musical that lovingly pokes fun at TV’s Friends, celebrating the adventures of your favorite group of 20-something friends as they navigate the pitfalls of work, life and love in 1990s Manhattan.

It’s a typical day at New York’s only coffee shop, Central Perk, until an unexpected runaway bride enters the picture and kicks the whole gang out of second gear! The new musical recreates our favorite moments from all 10 years of Friends through an uncensored, fast-paced, music-filled romp.

PERFORMANCE SCHEDULE
February 12th – March 3rd  
Tuesdays at 7:30PM 
Wednesdays at 2PM and 7:30PM (No matinee performance on Wed., Feb. 13)
Thursdays at 7:30PM 
Fridays at 7:30PM 
Saturdays at 2PM and 8PM
Sundays at 2:00PM (An additional performance will be held on Sun., Feb. 17 at 7:30PM)

title: "The Trial of Hippocrates"
description:
The Trial of Hippocrates: Interactive Courtroom Drama

The Trial of Hippocrates will be a unique, non-replicable evening of compelling and timely courtroom-style debate by reputable lawyers with proceedings and decisions by notable judges and jurors. Attendees are invited to participate by exploring the arguments of each side and submitting their guilty or not guilty vote to literally tip the scale and make their verdict heard. Following highly-acclaimed successes with The NHM Trials of Socrates, Antigone, and The Parthenon Marbles, the National Hellenic Museum once again partners with prominent judges and attorneys to take on another case with ancient roots and modern consequences. The case Hippocrates, the father of medicine, was called to the bedside of the dying King of Thebes. The physician saw immediately that nothing could cure this illness. The King offered the physician a herd of horses for his care, which Hippocrates accepted, offering a potion for fever. The fever subsided, replaced by boils. Once again, Hippocrates said there was nothing to do, yet the King demanded treatment. Gold was given for a salve. Vineyards and a villa offered for a potion. Despite treatments, the King grew worse and died. Hippocrates was arrested and brought before the King’s son and heir. The National Hellenic Museum asks: did Hippocrates violate his own oath? Is he guilty or not guilty? You decide at Harris Theater for Music and Dance in Chicago.

title: Chicago Opera Theater presents “The Scarlet Ibis”
description: COT presents the first major production of “The Scarlet Ibis.” It is a moving tale about brotherhood, nature and family. “The Scarlet Ibis” tells the story of Doodle, a young boy born physically disabled, and his relationship with his Brother in North Carolina against the backdrop of World War I. Composer Stefan Weisman and librettist David Cote adapted the magical 1960 short story by James Hurst for this new opera’s critically acclaimed first showing at 2015’s Prototype Festival with Beth Morrison Project. Chicago stage and movement director Elizabeth Margolius joins conductor and contemporary music expert David Hanlon to bring this story to life. Featuring Chicago mezzo-soprano Annie Rosen and countertenor Jordan Rutter, the production will be performed at the Studebaker Theater February 16, 21 and 24, 2018.

title: Sound Opinions featuring Sharon Van Etten
description:
End your work week a little early and join Jim DeRogatis & Greg Kot for a LIVE taping of Sound Opinions at Thalia Hall!
Sharon Van Etten returns to the show nearly seven years after her first appearance for an interview and performance! (Sharon Van Etten is also playing a sold out show at Thalia Hall later that night.)
Returning to her music career after nearly five years away, Van Etten’s fifth official album, Remind Me Tomorrow, embraces a bold new synthesizer-based sound. Jim and Greg gave it a rave review, comparing it to Radiohead’s sonic breakthrough on Kid A.
Join us for a beer and some free music from Sharon Van Etten. It's all happening on Friday, February 15th at Thalia Hall in Chicago. And it's FREE!! The recording will run from approximately 3:00 – 4:00 p.m. Please be there promptly at 2:45 p.m. to secure your spot.
Sponsored by Goose Island Beer Company
In partnership with Vocalo 91.1
PLEASE NOTE:
-This is a 21 and over event.
-The event is free but you NEED a ticket for entry.
-A TICKET DOESN'T GUARANTEE YOU ENTRANCE. Space will be given on a first come, first served basis. Please arrive promptly to make sure you get in.
-No late entries. The doors will close at 3:00pm.
Questions: interact@soundopinions.org

Visitors may now enjoy beverages on theatre tours!

title: Dan Navarro
description: With a career spanning decades Dan Navarro is perhaps best known as songwriter for artists as diverse as Jackson Browne, The Bangles, Keb’ Mo’ and Pat Benatar (the Grammy-nominated classic “We Belong”) to name a few. A multi-talented performer, Dan is a singer, a songwriter and a voice actor in major motion pictures, television series, & commercials. Having released a dozen albums – either solo and as Lowen&Navarro;, Dan Navarro released his first true studio-recorded solo album, "Shed My Skin" late last year and, as always, his songs are rich with insight and life experience, delivered straight-up, with honesty, grace and heart, in his moving and expressive baritone voice.

title: Yacht Party Chicago's Love Boat Booze Cruise
description:
Yacht Party Chicago's Love Boat Booze Cruise

Whether you're looking for love, or celebrating it, get out on this three story luxury yacht for a cruise on Lake Michigan. Tickets include a live DJ, dancing, giveaways, a drink at the after party and the best views of Chicago. title: Auditorium Theatre Historic Tours
description: Go behind the scenes of this National Historic Landmark, built by Dankmar Adler and Louis Sullivan, and view it as few do. Enjoy the radiant 24-karat gold-leafed ceiling arches, hundreds of Sullivan’s beautifully restored intricate stencil patterns, ornate gilded and bas-relief designs, and the endless floor and wall mosaics and murals by Charles Holloway and Albert Fleury. Visitors may now enjoy beverages on theatre tours!

title: Discover America - Program B: clarinet, violin, cello, and piano
description: Join The Chicago Ensemble for its 42nd season of eclectic classical chamber music performances, featuring Gerald Rizzer, artistic director/piano, and leading Chicago artists. Every concert offers a wide-ranging program of beloved masterworks, rarely heard gems, and contemporary works by composers around the world. Enjoy an intimate setting, complimentary reception, and informal spoken program notes that provide the perfect chamber music experience. This season, we have 4 traditional concerts(each performed twice) and 4 "Discover America" concerts (each performed once). Please PRINT the confirmation email/ticket and bring with you to the concert. Program B: clarinet, violin, cello, and piano Saturday, February 2, 2019 4:00pm, PianoForte in the south loop Matthew Browne For clarinet, violin, cello, and piano On the Immortality of a Crab Roger Zare For violin, cello, and piano Telescopic Variations Alexander Timofeev For clarinet and piano Phoenix Joyce Wai-chung Tang For clarinet, violin, and piano Reflections on Ariram Luzia von Wyl For violin, cello, and piano Autumn

title: Corey Smith Live at Joes on Weed St.
description: Corey Smith, the fan-made man, has sold over 1 million concert tickets, 1.5 million digital singles and over 220,000 albums.  Smith has amassed an unfailingly devout fan base, not only in his native Southeast region, but all around the nation, simply by telling it the way it is.  He has released 10 albums—including 2011’s Top 20 release The Broken Record.  Corey has written every word on every album himself and he produced 9 out of 10 of the records. In Summer 2015, Corey teamed up with producer Keith Stegall (Alan Jackson, Zac Brown Band) for his album, “While the Gettin’ Is Good,” which was released on Sugar Hill Records.  Smith’s concerts, which were documented on his last live record, Live in Chattanooga, regularly sell out, with audiences singing along to such fan favorites as the coming-of-age anthem “Twenty-One,” the nostalgic time warp “If I Could Do It Again” and the group hug “I Love Everyone.”   Corey consistently tours, hitting around 120 dates per year and has begun releasing singles from his upcoming project, the Great Wide Underground.

title: Shannon Nichol Lecture : Ordinary Landmarks
description:
Ordinary Landmarks: Designing public spaces to reintroduce locally regular landscapes into communities
The modern mobility of humans and building supplies, computer-aided design and detailing, the sweeping scale of the vehicular age, and an industrialized nursery industry are among the factors contributing to the odd uniformity and over-scaled feeling in much of our built environment.
Landscape architecture has not been immune to the pressures in recent decades to “go big” or “world class” in order to register an effective visual impact within this challenging, grandly scaled setting. Citing several projects designed by GGN over the last 20 years – including the Lurie Garden at Millennium Park and the Bill & Melinda Gates Foundation Campus -- Shannon Nichol will encourage “going small and going slow” to create a different type of landmark experience for both residents and visitors.
GGN’s work incorporates often-forgotten local ecologies and daily vernacular into prominent urban sites. GGN’s design process, which continues to heavily utilize hand-drawing as a design tool, will be shown, providing insight into a design firm working to retain complexity, idiosyncrasy, and natural nuance in the designed landscape. The importance of native plants, in resurfacing and repairing the unique, multi-thousand-year evolution of plants and animals in each place, will be discussed.
A handful of GGN's new monograph, GGN: Landscapes 1999–2018, will be available for purchase and autograph. There will be a small reception following the lecture for mingling and networking.
For this event: CEU/PDH 1.0 hour and it will be HSW.

title: Kinky Boots
description: Inspired by true events, KINKY BOOTS takes you from a gentlemen’s shoe factory in Northampton to the glamorous catwalks of Milan. Charlie Price is struggling to live up to his father’s expectations and continue the family business of Price & Son. With the factory’s future hanging in the balance, help arrives in the unlikely but spectacular form of Lola, a fabulous performer in need of some sturdy new stilettos. KINKY BOOTS has won every major Best Musical Award and is represented around the world with the Tony® Award-winning Broadway company (now in its sixth year), an Olivier Award-winning production in London, and a production in Germany. Other previous productions include a past US National Tour that played more than 80 cities, an Award-winning extended run in Toronto, a production in Australia, two productions in Korea, and a Japanese language production.

Deck chairs, lifeguard chairs, umbrellas and signage mimic the sensation of a day at the beach, complete with a pier from which onlookers can watch and revel in the installation below. title: The Beach Chicago | January 19, 2019 – February 3, 2019 | Free Public Art Installation
description: Conceived by New York- based designers, Snarkitecture, The Beach Chicago is an immersive installation comprised of a tall enclosure which creates a large, open room filled with more than a million antimicrobial and recyclable plastic balls. Deck chairs, lifeguard chairs, umbrellas and signage mimic the sensation of a day at the beach, complete with a pier from which onlookers can watch and revel in the installation below. The Beach Chicago is presented by Navy Pier and Expo Chicago, and supported the Chicago Free For All Fund at the Chicago Community Trust, Hilton Worldwide and the Navy Pier Associate Board. title: The Beach Chicago | January 19, 2019 – February 3, 2019 | Free Public Art Installation
description: Conceived by New York- based designers, Snarkitecture, The Beach Chicago is an immersive installation comprised of a tall enclosure which creates a large, open room filled with more than a million antimicrobial and recyclable plastic balls. Deck chairs, lifeguard chairs, umbrellas and signage mimic the sensation of a day at the beach, complete with a pier from which onlookers can watch and revel in the installation below. The Beach Chicago is presented by Navy Pier and Expo Chicago, and supported the Chicago Free For All Fund at the Chicago Community Trust, Hilton Worldwide and the Navy Pier Associate Board. Enjoy the radiant 24-karat gold-leafed ceiling arches, hundreds of Sullivan’s beautifully restored intricate stencil patterns, ornate gilded and bas-relief designs, and the endless floor and wall mosaics and murals by Charles Holloway and Albert Fleury. Visitors may now enjoy beverages on theatre tours!

title: Haymarket Pub & Brewery Clare's Thirsty Ale CAN Release & Tapping
description: We know you guys have a deep love for Clare's Thirsty, so to start off our 8th Beerthday right, we're having a Clare's Thirsty tapping & release party on January 12 & 13! It's our FIRST ever CANNING of this beer! Clare's Thirsty Ale - Bourbon Barrel Aged Imperial Stout with Raspberries 12%ABV 12oz cans @ $10 each (plus tax, can deposit in Michigan) Limit 4 per person. Duplicate orders will be cancelled. One ticket = 1 can. online sales start 12/1 at noon, and continue until sold out. We'll have draft available at the Pub & Taproom on 1/12 as well, so you can enjoy some while you're here to pick up!. Can pick up runs 1/12 & 1/13 from 11am-6pm local time. 21+ only, ID will be required at pick up. You will select a pickup location while checking out - Chicago or Michigan. Please read all the information below before purchasing your ticket. By purchasing your ticket, you agree to all of the terms below. Purchase Info: Ticket price is $10. One (1) ticket = one (1) 12oz can of Clare's Thirsty Ale. Buyer pays taxes and Eventbrite fees. Limit: There is a limit of four (4) tickets (4 cans) per person. Additional Info: All ticket sales are final. No refunds will be given. We will not allow proxies. In order to redeem your ticket, you must come to your chosen location. In order to purchase, you must be 21 years of age or older and must present a valid state issued ID, military ID, or passport at the time of pick up. FAQs: Will Clare's Thirsty Ale also be on tap? Yes. We will have it on tap starting at 11 am local time on 1/12 for both locations. It is available to ticket holders and to the general public. While supplies last. Where exactly do I pick up my bottle(s)? You must come to Haymarket Pub & Brewery (737 W. Randolph, Chicago, IL 60661) or Haymarket Brewery & Taproom (9301 Red Arrow Highway >>>FIll in the rest of the address!!! Do I have to bring a printed ticket to the event? No. Please arrive within the pick-up window with a valid state issued ID, military ID, or passport and we will check you in. Can I update my purchase information? No. No changes can be made after you have made your purchase. Please verify that all information is correct before purchasing. Is my ticket transferrable? No. We will not allow transferring of tickets. Is it ok if the registered name doesn't match the person who attends? No. The name on your ticket must match the name on your ID presented upon pick up. Is there a minimum age requirement to purchase a bottle? You must be 21 years of age or older. What's the refund policy? Sorry there are no refunds.

title: A&A; BALLET Auditions for “Sleeping Beauty”
description:
Audition attire: Girls: black camisole leotard, pink footed tights, pink canvas ballet and pointe shoes (age/level appropriate); Boys: black-footed tights, white tight fitted t-shirt, black ballet shoes. The audition will include dance movement and combinations to be performed in character. No preparation of audition material is necessary. Dancers will be notified via email within the week after the audition if they have been cast. A production fee will be required for dancers performing “Sleeping Beauty” and varies depending on role. Rehearsals begin on February 25 (for most of the parts) and will take place primarily on Saturdays at the American Rhythm Center. A pre-registration form may be downloaded at aacenterfordance.org. A&A; welcomes dancers from ages six to twenty-four to audition for various roles. 

“Sleeping Beauty” Princess Aurora who is fated to die from a prick to her finger on her sixteenth birthday because of a curse placed upon her at birth by a wicked fairy. A good fairy intervenes to alter the wicked fairy’s tragic spell: instead of dying, Princess Aurora, and her entire kingdom, will fall into a deep sleep. Only true love’s kiss will unleash the power to awaken her and the rest of her kingdom. This pinnacle of classical dance is heralded as ballet’s most sumptuous and artistically exacting masterpiece. Both the regal visual splendor and Tchaikovsky’s monumental score will enchant the entire family.
